00:02:12.140 --> 00:02:13.830 align:middle line:10%
And it's not just the world.

00:02:13.830 --> 00:02:16.520 align:middle line:90%
We are starving for something.

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:29.550 align:middle line:90%


00:02:29.550 --> 00:02:30.920 align:middle line:84%
PAUL HARRISON: When
I was about 20,

00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:34.440 align:middle line:84%
while I was sitting on my
desk, working on some problem,

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:37.710 align:middle line:84%
I experienced what I call
a shift in perspective.

00:02:37.710 --> 00:02:41.370 align:middle line:84%
What had seemed so elusive was
really right there front of me.

00:02:41.370 --> 00:02:43.950 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment,
I realized that what

00:02:43.950 --> 00:02:46.440 align:middle line:84%
I needed to do in
order to see it was

00:02:46.440 --> 00:02:49.450 align:middle line:90%
simply to shift my perspective.

00:02:49.450 --> 00:02:51.180 align:middle line:10%
It changed my whole life.

00:02:51.180 --> 00:02:53.000 align:middle line:10%
Because for once,
I finally got it.

00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.030 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I really got it.

00:02:54.030 --> 00:02:56.480 align:middle line:84%
And I understood
myself and I started

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:58.770 align:middle line:90%
to understand others better.

00:02:58.770 --> 00:02:59.510 align:middle line:90%
Hi.

00:02:59.510 --> 00:03:02.040 align:middle line:84%
I'm Paul Harrison, an
architect and an author.

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:04.580 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most common
questions I get asked

00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:08.060 align:middle line:84%
is why is an architect making
a movie about mindfulness.

00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:10.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's why I want to
share this story with you.

00:03:10.420 --> 00:03:13.410 align:middle line:84%
You see, I was a typical post
hippie generation teenager

00:03:13.410 --> 00:03:16.920 align:middle line:84%
from the early '70s with all
that reckless and mindless

00:03:16.920 --> 00:03:19.710 align:middle line:84%
behavior that made us
think we were really cool.

00:03:19.710 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:84%
And we loved to
challenge all the rules

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:24.994 align:middle line:84%
to the point of ending up with
some very serious consequences.

00:03:24.994 --> 00:03:26.027 align:middle line:90%
WOMAN (ON RADIO): Suspect down.

00:03:26.027 --> 00:03:28.130 align:middle line:90%
Request EMT immediately.

00:03:28.130 --> 00:03:31.200 align:middle line:84%
I realized once I
left high school that

00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:34.380 align:middle line:84%
was no path I wanted to stay
on and I was looking for a much

00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:36.840 align:middle line:84%
better way to deal
with stress, and family

00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:39.030 align:middle line:90%
issues, college, making money.

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:41.880 align:middle line:84%
And that led me to begin
practicing mindfulness.

00:03:41.880 --> 00:03:43.320 align:middle line:84%
And then about a
year and a half ago,

00:03:43.320 --> 00:03:44.910 align:middle line:84%
I set out on an
incredible journey

00:03:44.910 --> 00:03:48.850 align:middle line:84%
to find the core teachings of
what mindfulness really is.

00:03:48.850 --> 00:03:51.770 align:middle line:84%
You see, when I started, I
took the street wise approach.

00:03:51.770 --> 00:03:53.970 align:middle line:84%
I didn't want to
subscribe any one camp,

00:03:53.970 --> 00:03:57.410 align:middle line:84%
but rather find what that core
essence of mindfulness is.

00:03:57.410 --> 00:03:59.170 align:middle line:84%
I met with experts
like Ellen Langer

00:03:59.170 --> 00:04:01.860 align:middle line:84%
at Harvard, who many of called
the mother of mindfulness.

00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:05.060 align:middle line:84%
I also met with Congressman
Tim Ryan, Guy Claxton

00:04:05.060 --> 00:04:09.070 align:middle line:84%
from England, Jeffrey Schwartz,
psychiatrist, and even world

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:11.160 align:middle line:84%
renowned authors
like Dan Millman

00:04:11.160 --> 00:04:12.500 align:middle line:90%
from the "Peaceful Warrior."

00:04:12.500 --> 00:04:15.070 align:middle line:84%
And so my mission,
my passion, is

00:04:15.070 --> 00:04:17.220 align:middle line:84%
to share my journey
so you can start

00:04:17.220 --> 00:04:18.769 align:middle line:90%
learning about mindfulness.

00:04:18.769 --> 00:04:21.820 align:middle line:84%
And even more important,
to learn about yourself.

00:04:21.820 --> 00:04:33.584 align:middle line:90%


00:04:33.584 --> 00:04:35.250 align:middle line:84%
ELLEN LANGER (VOICEOVER):
So all certainty creates

00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:36.710 align:middle line:90%
an illusion of stability.

00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:38.710 align:middle line:84%
So certainty promotes
mindlessness.

00:04:38.710 --> 00:04:41.580 align:middle line:90%


00:04:41.580 --> 00:04:45.180 align:middle line:10%
Mindlessness usually
comes about by default.

00:04:45.180 --> 00:04:47.430 align:middle line:10%
And it's not
motivated, it just it

00:04:47.430 --> 00:04:51.160 align:middle line:10%
never occurred to you that this
thing could be other things.

00:04:51.160 --> 00:04:55.830 align:middle line:10%
Mindless mode is, I think, the
mode we're on 90% of the time.

00:04:55.830 --> 00:04:59.050 align:middle line:84%
Most of the time, we eat
and read the corn flakes box,

00:04:59.050 --> 00:05:02.430 align:middle line:84%
or we eat and talk, or eat
and dream, or most of us

00:05:02.430 --> 00:05:03.450 align:middle line:90%
eat and read.

00:05:03.450 --> 00:05:05.585 align:middle line:84%
Or we eat and watch TV.
-You get in the car.

00:05:05.585 --> 00:05:06.467 align:middle line:90%
You start the car.

00:05:06.467 --> 00:05:07.400 align:middle line:10%
Pull it out of the driveway.

00:05:07.400 --> 00:05:09.810 align:middle line:10%
You drive somewhere
for 10 or 15 minutes.

00:05:09.810 --> 00:05:12.080 align:middle line:10%
You arrive and you can't
remember how you got there.

00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:14.880 align:middle line:10%
You can take a cigarette out of
the pack, put it in your mouth,

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:18.590 align:middle line:10%
take out the lighter, light
it, and be completely unaware.

00:05:18.590 --> 00:05:22.570 align:middle line:84%
And you're going how-- and you
don't remember any of that.

00:05:22.570 --> 00:05:25.630 align:middle line:84%
Because you were
daydreaming the entire time.

00:05:25.630 --> 00:05:28.520 align:middle line:84%
And even when we're
not in that mode

00:05:28.520 --> 00:05:29.820 align:middle line:84%
because we're thinking
about something,

00:05:29.820 --> 00:05:32.384 align:middle line:84%
we're mindless about almost
everything else we're doing.

00:05:32.384 --> 00:05:33.850 align:middle line:84%
We aren't really aware
of 'em because we're

00:05:33.850 --> 00:05:37.791 align:middle line:84%
so busy onto the next thing,
anticipating the next thing.

00:05:37.791 --> 00:05:38.490 align:middle line:10%
And--

00:05:38.490 --> 00:05:42.190 align:middle line:10%
Mindfulness teachers
describe the distracted mind

00:05:42.190 --> 00:05:45.970 align:middle line:10%
as monkey mind, a monkey
that just jumps around

00:05:45.970 --> 00:05:47.580 align:middle line:10%
from one thing to the other.

00:05:47.580 --> 00:05:50.770 align:middle line:84%
We'll do something
to distract ourselves.

00:05:50.770 --> 00:05:53.340 align:middle line:84%
Because most of
us the get bored.

00:05:53.340 --> 00:05:54.320 align:middle line:90%
We get preoccupied.

00:05:54.320 --> 00:05:56.360 align:middle line:84%
We're on the computer
when we're at work.

00:05:56.360 --> 00:05:57.240 align:middle line:90%
We're just so distracted.

00:05:57.240 --> 00:05:59.930 align:middle line:84%
We'll put the radio on,
we'll put the TV on.

00:05:59.930 --> 00:06:01.450 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not watching it.

00:06:01.450 --> 00:06:02.807 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what channel it's on.

00:06:02.807 --> 00:06:04.140 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like
we're robots and we're

00:06:04.140 --> 00:06:05.310 align:middle line:90%
listening to this command.

00:06:05.310 --> 00:06:09.738 align:middle line:10%
And the robot can
only respond and react.

00:06:09.738 --> 00:06:16.515 align:middle line:90%


00:06:16.515 --> 00:06:18.115 align:middle line:84%
ROBINA COURTIN (VOICEOVER):
Mindfulness, for me,

00:06:18.115 --> 00:06:20.450 align:middle line:84%
is just a technique of
identifying what's there

00:06:20.450 --> 00:06:22.950 align:middle line:84%
and distinguishing between
the neurosis and the virtues,

00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.530 align:middle line:90%
or the good qualities.

00:06:25.530 --> 00:06:28.800 align:middle line:10%
The most common definition
is paying attention

00:06:28.800 --> 00:06:30.330 align:middle line:10%
to present moment experience.

00:06:30.330 --> 00:06:34.170 align:middle line:10%
Mindfulness is your
natural state of being.

00:06:34.170 --> 00:06:36.390 align:middle line:84%
It's the awakening
of possibility

00:06:36.390 --> 00:06:38.800 align:middle line:84%
and the possibility
of awakening.

00:06:38.800 --> 00:06:42.430 align:middle line:10%
But also, it's about just
noticing what is happening

00:06:42.430 --> 00:06:44.810 align:middle line:10%
every moment of the day.

00:06:44.810 --> 00:06:46.180 align:middle line:90%
Mindfulness is one thing.

00:06:46.180 --> 00:06:47.380 align:middle line:90%
It's paying attention.

00:06:47.380 --> 00:06:50.100 align:middle line:84%
To the actions
that you are taking.

00:06:50.100 --> 00:06:52.870 align:middle line:10%
It's a sustained
quality of being present.

00:06:52.870 --> 00:06:55.630 align:middle line:84%
It's like being in the zone
and you can actually train

00:06:55.630 --> 00:06:57.840 align:middle line:90%
your mind to be in the zone.

00:06:57.840 --> 00:07:00.270 align:middle line:10%
I call it a basic mind hygiene.

00:07:00.270 --> 00:07:03.700 align:middle line:84%
A clear minded
observational perspective.

00:07:03.700 --> 00:07:05.350 align:middle line:90%
The experience of mindfulness--

00:07:05.350 --> 00:07:07.910 align:middle line:84%
Is turning into
reality as it is,

00:07:07.910 --> 00:07:09.820 align:middle line:90%
as it unfolds simply right now.

00:07:09.820 --> 00:07:12.690 align:middle line:84%
Which is just really the
full experience of life.

00:07:12.690 --> 00:07:15.640 align:middle line:84%
Without getting lost in
thought and becoming forgetful.

00:07:15.640 --> 00:07:18.620 align:middle line:84%
Thoughts are
representations of reality.

00:07:18.620 --> 00:07:20.820 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness is the
actual experience.

00:07:20.820 --> 00:07:26.190 align:middle line:84%
Is the ability to
go to color white.

00:07:26.190 --> 00:07:29.560 align:middle line:84%
So mindfulness is paying
attention to the moment

00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:33.850 align:middle line:84%
with an open and a willingness
to let go of old patterns

00:07:33.850 --> 00:07:35.978 align:middle line:90%
and live in the present.

00:07:35.978 --> 00:07:36.954 align:middle line:90%
Did you get it?

