00:08:55.420 --> 00:08:57.520 align:middle line:84%
JUN PO DENNIS KELLY (VOICEOVER):
Go deep enough into witnessing

00:08:57.520 --> 00:08:59.440 align:middle line:90%
and observe the function of ego.

00:08:59.440 --> 00:09:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And you'll discover that
it's just continually

00:09:01.520 --> 00:09:05.547 align:middle line:90%
running reactive loops."

00:09:05.547 --> 00:09:06.680 align:middle line:84%
PAUL HARRISON: We
don't experience

00:09:06.680 --> 00:09:08.510 align:middle line:90%
reality as it really as.

00:09:08.510 --> 00:09:12.600 align:middle line:84%
We perceive it through a filter
that allows us to see only what

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:14.390 align:middle line:90%
we've been conditioned to see.

00:09:14.390 --> 00:09:18.270 align:middle line:84%
That's because we've become
trapped in the neurobiology

00:09:18.270 --> 00:09:20.040 align:middle line:90%
of our own brain.

00:09:20.040 --> 00:09:22.590 align:middle line:84%
Just like every tree has
a unique set of branches,

00:09:22.590 --> 00:09:26.350 align:middle line:84%
every brain has a unique pattern
of neurons and connections

00:09:26.350 --> 00:09:29.630 align:middle line:84%
that are both genetic
and learned over time.

00:09:29.630 --> 00:09:33.480 align:middle line:84%
So each and every one of
us is wired differently.

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:36.160 align:middle line:84%
And it's the neural
architecture of our brains

00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:38.610 align:middle line:84%
that tells us who we
are and how we're going

00:09:38.610 --> 00:09:40.480 align:middle line:90%
to act and react in the world.

00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:42.530 align:middle line:84%
Every thought we
have is the result

00:09:42.530 --> 00:09:45.600 align:middle line:84%
of a network of hundreds
of billions of brain cells

00:09:45.600 --> 00:09:46.950 align:middle line:90%
called neurons.

00:09:46.950 --> 00:09:50.940 align:middle line:84%
Unlike other cells in our body,
neurons don't touch each other,

00:09:50.940 --> 00:09:55.760 align:middle line:84%
but are separated by microscopic
spaces called synapses.

00:09:55.760 --> 00:09:57.900 align:middle line:84%
Neurons communicate
across these synapses

00:09:57.900 --> 00:10:02.050 align:middle line:84%
through chemical transfers that
blast from one cell to the next

00:10:02.050 --> 00:10:03.820 align:middle line:90%
with a zap of electricity.

00:10:03.820 --> 00:10:07.780 align:middle line:84%
Messages zip around our brain
like a supersonic pinball

00:10:07.780 --> 00:10:08.580 align:middle line:90%
machine.

00:10:08.580 --> 00:10:10.860 align:middle line:10%
Each neuron sends and
receives information

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:14.600 align:middle line:10%
to 50,000 other neurons
in a rapid fire production

00:10:14.600 --> 00:10:18.810 align:middle line:10%
that all adds up to
100 billion neurons

00:10:18.810 --> 00:10:21.860 align:middle line:10%
times 50,000 connections.

00:10:21.860 --> 00:10:24.060 align:middle line:10%
In fact, there are
more connections

00:10:24.060 --> 00:10:26.630 align:middle line:10%
between neurons in a single
human brain than there

00:10:26.630 --> 00:10:28.970 align:middle line:10%
are stars in our galaxy.

00:10:28.970 --> 00:10:31.260 align:middle line:84%
The result is a
complex neural forest

00:10:31.260 --> 00:10:34.380 align:middle line:84%
of networks that
form our personality,

00:10:34.380 --> 00:10:36.980 align:middle line:90%
our identity, and our habits.

00:10:36.980 --> 00:10:39.900 align:middle line:84%
Hardly ever do we find
trees that grow alike

00:10:39.900 --> 00:10:42.940 align:middle line:84%
and we don't find
brains that grow alike.

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:45.050 align:middle line:90%
We are all unique.

00:10:45.050 --> 00:10:47.540 align:middle line:10%
While these trillions
of neuron networks

00:10:47.540 --> 00:10:51.520 align:middle line:10%
often work in concert to create
brainstorms of creativity

00:10:51.520 --> 00:10:54.500 align:middle line:10%
and new ideas, their
primary purpose

00:10:54.500 --> 00:10:57.830 align:middle line:10%
is to keep each and every
one of us alive and safe

00:10:57.830 --> 00:11:02.120 align:middle line:10%
by recognizing patterns as
they access a constantly

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.110 align:middle line:10%
changing environment.

00:11:04.110 --> 00:11:07.470 align:middle line:90%
But sometimes, things get stuck.

00:11:07.470 --> 00:11:10.330 align:middle line:90%


00:11:10.330 --> 00:11:13.760 align:middle line:84%
Who, of us, doesn't have some
form of addictive behavior

00:11:13.760 --> 00:11:14.540 align:middle line:90%
or another?

00:11:14.540 --> 00:11:18.040 align:middle line:84%
Maybe for a-- for
personal comfort,

00:11:18.040 --> 00:11:21.110 align:middle line:84%
or because of a desire,
or whatever is behind it,

00:11:21.110 --> 00:11:24.820 align:middle line:84%
and changing them is very
difficult for a lot of people

00:11:24.820 --> 00:11:25.910 align:middle line:90%
and they struggle with that.

00:11:25.910 --> 00:11:29.710 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of them are stuck
in old routines, old patterns.

00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:32.650 align:middle line:84%
Eventually, we becomes
stuck in these patterns

00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:34.550 align:middle line:84%
and live our lives
on auto pilot.

00:11:34.550 --> 00:11:37.110 align:middle line:84%
Essentially, becoming
more and more mindless

00:11:37.110 --> 00:11:40.170 align:middle line:84%
as we continue to view
the world through filters

00:11:40.170 --> 00:11:43.630 align:middle line:84%
instead of seeing things
as they really are.

00:11:43.630 --> 00:11:47.090 align:middle line:84%
As we grow older, our
actions and reactions become

00:11:47.090 --> 00:11:50.810 align:middle line:84%
conditioned by our hopes,
our tensions, anxieties,

00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:53.360 align:middle line:84%
motivations, loves,
hates, desires,

00:11:53.360 --> 00:11:54.810 align:middle line:90%
fears, or frustrations.

00:11:54.810 --> 00:11:57.750 align:middle line:84%
Thus, we analyze
before we experience.

00:11:57.750 --> 00:11:59.700 align:middle line:90%
And we filter before we see.

00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:02.880 align:middle line:10%
Explaining that in brain terms
is not hard to understand.

00:12:02.880 --> 00:12:06.110 align:middle line:10%
I've done it in a lot of my
writing, which is we have

00:12:06.110 --> 00:12:08.060 align:middle line:10%
habits centers in our brain.

00:12:08.060 --> 00:12:10.130 align:middle line:84%
These habit centers
in our brain,

00:12:10.130 --> 00:12:13.280 align:middle line:84%
roughly, are shared
with reptiles.

00:12:13.280 --> 00:12:16.350 align:middle line:90%
And they are very unconscious.

00:12:16.350 --> 00:12:21.270 align:middle line:84%
So you literally do get into
behavioral loops that are your

00:12:21.270 --> 00:12:23.720 align:middle line:90%
doing without you aware of it.

00:12:23.720 --> 00:12:26.710 align:middle line:84%
Our perception operates
increasingly like a defense

00:12:26.710 --> 00:12:30.070 align:middle line:84%
mechanism, trapping us in
patterns of behavior that

00:12:30.070 --> 00:12:32.700 align:middle line:84%
have less to do
with present reality

00:12:32.700 --> 00:12:35.662 align:middle line:84%
and more to do with past
experience or expectations.

00:12:35.662 --> 00:12:37.990 align:middle line:84%
But if we start changing
that neural architecture

00:12:37.990 --> 00:12:40.250 align:middle line:84%
through intentionally paying
attention to what's here

00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:42.110 align:middle line:84%
in a particular
way, then we start

00:12:42.110 --> 00:12:43.420 align:middle line:84%
training that
healthy reactivity,

00:12:43.420 --> 00:12:46.020 align:middle line:90%
that more adaptive reactivity.

00:12:46.020 --> 00:12:48.630 align:middle line:84%
That can help us with
stress, anxiety, depression,

00:12:48.630 --> 00:12:51.340 align:middle line:90%
trauma, and even addiction.

00:12:51.340 --> 00:12:54.830 align:middle line:84%
As long as we continue to
perceive reality as we've been

00:12:54.830 --> 00:12:57.100 align:middle line:84%
conditioned to
perceive it, we're

00:12:57.100 --> 00:13:00.230 align:middle line:84%
destined to live a life
in endless reactive

00:13:00.230 --> 00:13:02.510 align:middle line:90%
loops of conditioned responses.

00:13:02.510 --> 00:13:06.970 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness changes your
relationship with that habit

00:13:06.970 --> 00:13:09.830 align:middle line:84%
center so that it's not
in control in anything

00:13:09.830 --> 00:13:10.960 align:middle line:90%
like the same degree.

00:13:10.960 --> 00:13:14.100 align:middle line:84%
By noticing the
looping that happens

00:13:14.100 --> 00:13:17.550 align:middle line:84%
in any particular moment,
that reactive looping,

00:13:17.550 --> 00:13:20.160 align:middle line:84%
that's sending us into
these states of suffering.

00:13:20.160 --> 00:13:23.430 align:middle line:84%
But if you practice
mindfulness once or twice

00:13:23.430 --> 00:13:26.430 align:middle line:84%
daily, you'll be able to
change your brain physiology

00:13:26.430 --> 00:13:29.180 align:middle line:84%
and you'll be able to
change your nervous system.

00:13:29.180 --> 00:13:30.880 align:middle line:84%
Even eight minutes
or more a day

00:13:30.880 --> 00:13:32.960 align:middle line:84%
can grow measurable
neural structure.

00:13:32.960 --> 00:13:36.330 align:middle line:84%
So anything in the brain that
is changing and being retained

00:13:36.330 --> 00:13:38.330 align:middle line:84%
is through some kind
of neuroplasticity.

00:13:38.330 --> 00:13:40.690 align:middle line:84%
And again, it's not
rewiring major pathways.

00:13:40.690 --> 00:13:42.200 align:middle line:10%
It's changing the
subtle connectivity

00:13:42.200 --> 00:13:44.020 align:middle line:10%
of the pathways that exist.

00:13:44.020 --> 00:13:47.010 align:middle line:84%
So neuroplasticity
changes the brain

00:13:47.010 --> 00:13:51.340 align:middle line:84%
from being more centered in
primary emotion, the kind

00:13:51.340 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:84%
of emotion that we share
with all the other mammals

00:13:53.660 --> 00:13:57.140 align:middle line:84%
to the executive
centers of the brain.

00:13:57.140 --> 00:14:00.890 align:middle line:10%
We do form new neurons,
new connections.

00:14:00.890 --> 00:14:04.050 align:middle line:84%
So when you practice
mindfulness,

00:14:04.050 --> 00:14:06.240 align:middle line:90%
then we develop new circuits.

00:14:06.240 --> 00:14:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Neurons that fire
together are wired together

00:14:08.450 --> 00:14:10.200 align:middle line:84%
throughout the entire
nervous system.

00:14:10.200 --> 00:14:12.910 align:middle line:84%
They do so preferentially
for what's in the field

00:14:12.910 --> 00:14:13.950 align:middle line:90%
of focused attention.

00:14:13.950 --> 00:14:17.560 align:middle line:84%
The brain is more plastic, even
in adults, than people realize.

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:20.100 align:middle line:84%
I mean there is a lot
of room for change

00:14:20.100 --> 00:14:20.970 align:middle line:90%
in those habit loops.

00:14:20.970 --> 00:14:22.990 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't-- it
does not take that long.

00:14:22.990 --> 00:14:27.560 align:middle line:84%
So little mindfulness
practices sustained over time

00:14:27.560 --> 00:14:31.110 align:middle line:84%
can add up to big
changes for the better

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:32.740 align:middle line:90%
over the course of your life.

00:14:32.740 --> 00:14:33.665 align:middle line:90%
The brain is plastic.

00:14:33.665 --> 00:14:37.130 align:middle line:10%
And what it has
learned, it can unlearn.

00:14:37.130 --> 00:14:40.160 align:middle line:84%
So becoming mindful means
untraining our brains,

00:14:40.160 --> 00:14:42.740 align:middle line:84%
emptying them of
preconceived patterns.

00:14:42.740 --> 00:14:47.010 align:middle line:84%
This easily accessible ability
releases us from constraints

00:14:47.010 --> 00:14:49.640 align:middle line:84%
and quickly changes
mindless behavior

00:14:49.640 --> 00:14:50.920 align:middle line:90%
in to mindful behavior.

00:14:50.920 --> 00:14:53.310 align:middle line:84%
But what's more important
is that mindfulness

00:14:53.310 --> 00:14:54.940 align:middle line:90%
actually evolves the brain.

00:14:54.940 --> 00:14:58.290 align:middle line:84%
It actually advances
the evolutionary process

00:14:58.290 --> 00:15:02.530 align:middle line:84%
of our brain to a state
where we act in a wiser more

00:15:02.530 --> 00:15:05.780 align:middle line:84%
compassionate mode,
to not only ourselves,

00:15:05.780 --> 00:15:07.720 align:middle line:84%
but to others in our
global environment.

00:15:07.720 --> 00:15:11.350 align:middle line:90%


00:15:11.350 --> 00:15:12.970 align:middle line:10%
So I think if we
leave around 5:00 PM,

00:15:12.970 --> 00:15:14.430 align:middle line:10%
we should be there around 9-ish.

00:15:14.430 --> 00:15:15.440 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:15.440 --> 00:15:16.580 align:middle line:90%
That sounds good.

00:15:16.580 --> 00:15:17.450 align:middle line:90%
Are you excited?

00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:18.150 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:18.150 --> 00:15:19.000 align:middle line:90%
What about you?

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:19.810 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:15:19.810 --> 00:15:22.490 align:middle line:84%
I've been waiting
to go for so long.

00:15:22.490 --> 00:15:23.840 align:middle line:90%
Are you going to bring anything?

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:26.060 align:middle line:90%
Um, like what?

00:15:26.060 --> 00:15:28.762 align:middle line:90%
Like a surprise.

00:15:28.762 --> 00:15:29.580 align:middle line:90%
A surprise?

00:15:29.580 --> 00:15:30.850 align:middle line:90%
[PHONE RINGING]

00:15:30.850 --> 00:15:33.000 align:middle line:84%
I think it would be
nice to get a surprise.

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:35.085 align:middle line:84%
Well, like, if I told
you it was a surprise,

00:15:35.085 --> 00:15:37.380 align:middle line:84%
then it wouldn't,
like, be a surprise.

00:15:37.380 --> 00:15:39.010 align:middle line:84%
I know, but I was
just give you a

00:15:39.010 --> 00:15:42.096 align:middle line:84%
heads up that maybe it would be
nice to get a surprise is all.

00:15:42.096 --> 00:15:43.630 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:15:43.630 --> 00:15:44.370 align:middle line:90%
Well--

00:15:44.370 --> 00:15:45.670 align:middle line:84%
Why do you keep
checking your phone?

00:15:45.670 --> 00:15:47.740 align:middle line:90%
I don't keep checking my phone.

00:15:47.740 --> 00:15:48.740 align:middle line:90%
Sure, you do.

00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:50.640 align:middle line:84%
I pay attention to
everything you do

00:15:50.640 --> 00:15:51.850 align:middle line:90%
and you keep checking it.

00:15:51.850 --> 00:15:53.761 align:middle line:84%
It's a bad habit and
it's completely mindless.

00:15:53.761 --> 00:15:56.120 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah?
Well, so what-- what if it is?

00:15:56.120 --> 00:15:57.440 align:middle line:90%
What if it's a bad habit?

00:15:57.440 --> 00:15:59.470 align:middle line:84%
Because I need
your full attention.

00:15:59.470 --> 00:16:01.210 align:middle line:84%
And look, now you're
getting defensive about it.

00:16:01.210 --> 00:16:03.970 align:middle line:84%
It's your reactive loops like
swinging all out of control.

00:16:03.970 --> 00:16:05.670 align:middle line:90%
You don't even realize it.

00:16:05.670 --> 00:16:06.890 align:middle line:90%
Reactive what?

00:16:06.890 --> 00:16:07.960 align:middle line:90%
Reactive loops.

00:16:07.960 --> 00:16:10.990 align:middle line:84%
It's when you react to the
same thing over and over again.

00:16:10.990 --> 00:16:12.260 align:middle line:90%
Do you realize you're doing it?

00:16:12.260 --> 00:16:13.310 align:middle line:90%
Well, yeah, now I do.

00:16:13.310 --> 00:16:14.870 align:middle line:10%
Thanks for you
pointing that out.

00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:16.586 align:middle line:84%
I realize it.
Yeah.

00:16:16.586 --> 00:16:17.285 align:middle line:90%
You're welcome.

00:16:17.285 --> 00:16:24.970 align:middle line:90%


00:16:24.970 --> 00:16:26.980 align:middle line:84%
Now recent research
in cognitive science

00:16:26.980 --> 00:16:31.200 align:middle line:84%
has confirmed that performance
increases when we think less.

00:16:31.200 --> 00:16:33.980 align:middle line:84%
If a tennis player were to
think of a where a ball might be

00:16:33.980 --> 00:16:37.150 align:middle line:84%
instead of seeing where
that ball actually is,

00:16:37.150 --> 00:16:39.360 align:middle line:84%
it would be too late
and he'd miss it.

00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:41.800 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness enables
us to respond quickly

00:16:41.800 --> 00:16:45.243 align:middle line:84%
and effortlessly to attain peak
performance in any situation.

00:16:45.243 --> 00:16:51.310 align:middle line:90%


00:16:51.310 --> 00:16:55.010 align:middle line:10%
Trying is a really interesting
phenomenon because to try to do

00:16:55.010 --> 00:16:56.480 align:middle line:10%
something is to not do it.

00:16:56.480 --> 00:16:58.950 align:middle line:10%
We're trying to do things,
rather than just doing things.

00:16:58.950 --> 00:17:00.950 align:middle line:10%
If I said to somebody could
I have a glass of water

00:17:00.950 --> 00:17:02.970 align:middle line:10%
and they said I'll try to
get you a glass of water,

00:17:02.970 --> 00:17:04.319 align:middle line:10%
that wouldn't make much sense.

00:17:04.319 --> 00:17:06.609 align:middle line:90%
What does trying look like?

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:09.900 align:middle line:84%
And it looks like this.
-Try not.

00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:11.119 align:middle line:90%
There is no trying.

00:17:11.119 --> 00:17:12.569 align:middle line:90%
Just do or do not.

00:17:12.569 --> 00:17:14.599 align:middle line:90%
Which is actually very trying.

00:17:14.599 --> 00:17:18.180 align:middle line:84%
To be-- to be in that
state of kind of having

00:17:18.180 --> 00:17:19.470 align:middle line:90%
to look like you're trying.

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:22.230 align:middle line:84%
And accept whatever
you do is fine for now.

00:17:22.230 --> 00:17:23.599 align:middle line:90%
We'll get better over time.

00:17:23.599 --> 00:17:25.579 align:middle line:90%
So don't try to do anything.

00:17:25.579 --> 00:17:29.990 align:middle line:10%
A very good example I think
is from the film "Matrix."

00:17:29.990 --> 00:17:33.590 align:middle line:84%
There is this moment
when Morpheus and Neo

00:17:33.590 --> 00:17:35.700 align:middle line:90%
having a kung fu sparring.

00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:39.860 align:middle line:84%
And Morpheus says don't
try to hit me and hit me.

00:17:39.860 --> 00:17:41.830 align:middle line:84%
That's exactly-- you know,
we're trying to do things,

00:17:41.830 --> 00:17:44.190 align:middle line:90%
rather than just doing things.

00:17:44.190 --> 00:17:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And mindfulness teaches
us how to do things

00:17:46.910 --> 00:17:48.180 align:middle line:90%
without trying to do things.

00:17:48.180 --> 00:17:49.910 align:middle line:84%
When you prepare
for an interview

00:17:49.910 --> 00:17:52.950 align:middle line:84%
and you go into the interview
and then they ask you questions

00:17:52.950 --> 00:17:54.630 align:middle line:84%
that you haven't
prepared for, and you're

00:17:54.630 --> 00:17:56.830 align:middle line:84%
sort of thrown because
you're there ready

00:17:56.830 --> 00:17:58.510 align:middle line:90%
made with your answers.

00:17:58.510 --> 00:17:59.990 align:middle line:84%
And you don't do a
very good job of it.

00:17:59.990 --> 00:18:02.410 align:middle line:84%
And then when you come
out of the interview

00:18:02.410 --> 00:18:04.320 align:middle line:84%
and you're walking
down the stairs

00:18:04.320 --> 00:18:07.160 align:middle line:84%
and you have what the
French [SPEAKING FRENCH].

00:18:07.160 --> 00:18:10.410 align:middle line:84%
It's like, oh, yeah, I
should have said that.

00:18:10.410 --> 00:18:12.570 align:middle line:84%
I should have-- oh, that's
what I should have done.

00:18:12.570 --> 00:18:16.380 align:middle line:84%
It's like then you-- then you
get your intelligence back.

00:18:16.380 --> 00:18:19.010 align:middle line:84%
Before the interview,
before you were wise,

00:18:19.010 --> 00:18:23.594 align:middle line:84%
and afterwards you are wise, but
in between, you are otherwise.

00:18:23.594 --> 00:18:25.900 align:middle line:84%
And otherwise means
it's like you're trying.

00:18:25.900 --> 00:18:28.910 align:middle line:84%
You're trying to
find something clever

00:18:28.910 --> 00:18:33.315 align:middle line:84%
which you bring to the
situation and want to use.

00:18:33.315 --> 00:18:36.070 align:middle line:90%


00:18:36.070 --> 00:18:38.000 align:middle line:84%
But I think we're
able to achieve

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:41.380 align:middle line:84%
with the mindfulness training
is the best of both worlds.

00:18:41.380 --> 00:18:43.630 align:middle line:84%
The alertness of the
central nervous system

00:18:43.630 --> 00:18:47.380 align:middle line:84%
without the anxiety
and the calm relaxation

00:18:47.380 --> 00:18:50.100 align:middle line:84%
and pleasantness of the
parasympathetic system

00:18:50.100 --> 00:18:51.400 align:middle line:90%
without the drowsiness.

00:18:51.400 --> 00:18:53.190 align:middle line:84%
So there was an
interesting study

00:18:53.190 --> 00:18:56.340 align:middle line:84%
where they were in the scanner,
during the same experiment,

00:18:56.340 --> 00:18:58.090 align:middle line:84%
and they were presented
with the digits

00:18:58.090 --> 00:19:00.330 align:middle line:90%
on the screen between 1 and 9.

00:19:00.330 --> 00:19:03.750 align:middle line:84%
And they had to judge whether
the digit was odd or even.

00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:06.140 align:middle line:84%
So as you can imagine,
it's a simple task.

00:19:06.140 --> 00:19:08.390 align:middle line:84%
You don't need to
think about it much.

00:19:08.390 --> 00:19:11.230 align:middle line:84%
But they noticed
in the data here,

00:19:11.230 --> 00:19:13.280 align:middle line:84%
you can see the
brain is on fire.

00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:15.740 align:middle line:84%
The prefrontal
cortex is engaged.

00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:17.430 align:middle line:84%
A lot of visual
cortex is engaged.

00:19:17.430 --> 00:19:19.210 align:middle line:90%
Motor cortex is engaged.

00:19:19.210 --> 00:19:20.730 align:middle line:90%
I called it ego effort.

00:19:20.730 --> 00:19:23.305 align:middle line:84%
This person has a
very strong sense of I

00:19:23.305 --> 00:19:24.910 align:middle line:90%
really need to do this task.

00:19:24.910 --> 00:19:26.245 align:middle line:90%
I'm really going to go for it.

00:19:26.245 --> 00:19:27.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do it well.

00:19:27.540 --> 00:19:30.320 align:middle line:84%
Behaviorally, they're
performing on the same level.

00:19:30.320 --> 00:19:33.710 align:middle line:84%
It's a simple task, what we
call on the ceiling level,

00:19:33.710 --> 00:19:35.900 align:middle line:90%
so both performing well.

00:19:35.900 --> 00:19:39.550 align:middle line:84%
But what happening with the
experienced meditator, only

00:19:39.550 --> 00:19:43.100 align:middle line:84%
absolutely essential bits of
the brain for the performance

00:19:43.100 --> 00:19:44.440 align:middle line:90%
of this task.

00:19:44.440 --> 00:19:47.350 align:middle line:84%
So one is expending
a lot of energy

00:19:47.350 --> 00:19:50.066 align:middle line:84%
to do the same task, whereas the
other one, just, you can say,

00:19:50.066 --> 00:19:50.980 align:middle line:90%
in the state of flow.

00:19:50.980 --> 00:19:54.490 align:middle line:90%


00:19:54.490 --> 00:19:55.300 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I don't get it.

00:19:55.300 --> 00:19:57.290 align:middle line:90%
Like, I try stuff all the time.

00:19:57.290 --> 00:19:58.065 align:middle line:90%
You don't get it?

00:19:58.065 --> 00:19:58.765 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:19:58.765 --> 00:19:59.722 align:middle line:90%
I don't get it.

00:19:59.722 --> 00:20:00.990 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:20:00.990 --> 00:20:03.080 align:middle line:90%
Try to take this pen from me.

00:20:03.080 --> 00:20:04.776 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:20:04.776 --> 00:20:06.805 align:middle line:84%
See, you weren't
paying attention.

00:20:06.805 --> 00:20:08.220 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:20:08.220 --> 00:20:09.350 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:20:09.350 --> 00:20:11.746 align:middle line:90%
Try to take the pen from me.

00:20:11.746 --> 00:20:12.702 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:20:12.702 --> 00:20:14.301 align:middle line:84%
See, you're not
paying attention.

00:20:14.301 --> 00:20:17.000 align:middle line:84%
-Well--
-I said try to take the pen.

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.760 align:middle line:90%
I didn't say take the pen.

00:20:18.760 --> 00:20:19.930 align:middle line:90%
Well, what do you mean?

00:20:19.930 --> 00:20:21.780 align:middle line:90%
Well, trying is not doing.

00:20:21.780 --> 00:20:23.190 align:middle line:84%
Hold the pen.
-OK.

00:20:23.190 --> 00:20:27.051 align:middle line:90%


00:20:27.051 --> 00:20:27.750 align:middle line:90%
See?

00:20:27.750 --> 00:20:29.140 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to take
the pen, but I'm

00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:31.700 align:middle line:90%
not actually taking the pen.

00:20:31.700 --> 00:20:32.640 align:middle line:90%
Remember?

00:20:32.640 --> 00:20:36.051 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness teaches
you to do, not try.

00:20:36.051 --> 00:20:39.650 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
I mean, maybe.

00:20:39.650 --> 00:20:40.980 align:middle line:10%
Maybe you'll
remember the next time

00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:44.426 align:middle line:10%
you try to meet me on time.
-Yeah, maybe.

00:20:44.426 --> 00:20:54.320 align:middle line:90%


00:20:54.320 --> 00:20:58.030 align:middle line:10%
The essence of mindfulness
is to observe what's there

00:20:58.030 --> 00:21:00.800 align:middle line:10%
and what we bring
that observation to,

00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:03.440 align:middle line:10%
with the quality of being
aware of our own awareness.

00:21:03.440 --> 00:21:05.880 align:middle line:84%
Which is sort of the opposite
of being absent-minded.

00:21:05.880 --> 00:21:09.150 align:middle line:84%
It's like dedicating
your awareness

00:21:09.150 --> 00:21:11.440 align:middle line:90%
to the present moment.

00:21:11.440 --> 00:21:13.940 align:middle line:10%
You're either mindful
in your whole body

00:21:13.940 --> 00:21:17.920 align:middle line:10%
and in your interactions or
you're sleep and unconscious.

00:21:17.920 --> 00:21:20.780 align:middle line:10%
And there's nothing like
a close relationship

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:24.350 align:middle line:10%
to show you, to mirror, what
your unconscious patterns are.

00:21:24.350 --> 00:21:27.060 align:middle line:10%
So first step is to
just be with what's

00:21:27.060 --> 00:21:30.210 align:middle line:10%
there, which means that all
that's there is mindfulness.

00:21:30.210 --> 00:21:31.380 align:middle line:90%
We're just aware of it.

00:21:31.380 --> 00:21:34.600 align:middle line:84%
We're paying attention, being
present, rather than being

00:21:34.600 --> 00:21:36.430 align:middle line:90%
distracted by so many thoughts.

00:21:36.430 --> 00:21:38.460 align:middle line:10%
If you want to
summarize it, mindfulness

00:21:38.460 --> 00:21:41.580 align:middle line:10%
allows you to be
authentically present

00:21:41.580 --> 00:21:45.190 align:middle line:10%
without the interference
of preoccupations

00:21:45.190 --> 00:21:47.000 align:middle line:10%
about the past or the future.

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:50.440 align:middle line:84%
So baby that's
born, as it were,

00:21:50.440 --> 00:21:53.220 align:middle line:84%
would not be presumed to
be mindful necessarily.

00:21:53.220 --> 00:21:57.100 align:middle line:84%
Because mindfulness involves
this sustained deliberate

00:21:57.100 --> 00:21:58.482 align:middle line:90%
quality of recollectiveness.

00:21:58.482 --> 00:22:01.560 align:middle line:10%
It's the capacity of
human beings to be aware.

00:22:01.560 --> 00:22:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And our human
awareness can be focused

00:22:03.470 --> 00:22:05.300 align:middle line:90%
in something we call attention.

00:22:05.300 --> 00:22:09.050 align:middle line:84%
So being able to be
attentive to what we're

00:22:09.050 --> 00:22:11.590 align:middle line:84%
doing, which is the
essence of mindfulness,

00:22:11.590 --> 00:22:12.730 align:middle line:90%
is incredibly helpful.

00:22:12.730 --> 00:22:16.770 align:middle line:10%
We just are operating in an
incomplete field of awareness.

00:22:16.770 --> 00:22:20.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not sure the field of
awareness can ever be complete,

00:22:20.590 --> 00:22:21.940 align:middle line:90%
but it can be much faster.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:24.370 align:middle line:10%
And it makes you
mindful of these very

00:22:24.370 --> 00:22:27.130 align:middle line:10%
fundamental physical processes.

00:22:27.130 --> 00:22:30.700 align:middle line:84%
And it makes you feel more
grounded in your own body.

00:22:30.700 --> 00:22:33.110 align:middle line:84%
So when you
practice mindfulness,

00:22:33.110 --> 00:22:35.420 align:middle line:84%
you're not only becoming
more aware of things

00:22:35.420 --> 00:22:36.680 align:middle line:84%
that before you
weren't aware of,

00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:39.050 align:middle line:84%
but you're developing
these skills that can allow

00:22:39.050 --> 00:22:40.730 align:middle line:90%
you to sense the inner world.

00:22:40.730 --> 00:22:41.840 align:middle line:90%
Awareness is change.

00:22:41.840 --> 00:22:44.468 align:middle line:90%
It is the action of change.

00:22:44.468 --> 00:22:48.810 align:middle line:84%
And we need to awaken the
mind, expand out sense of self

00:22:48.810 --> 00:22:53.550 align:middle line:84%
to really alert our attention,
to expand our awareness.

00:22:53.550 --> 00:22:55.820 align:middle line:84%
And you can use mindfulness
as a process to do it.

00:22:55.820 --> 00:23:00.740 align:middle line:10%
So once you're aware of
that, you can change it.

00:23:00.740 --> 00:23:03.510 align:middle line:84%
Until you're aware of
it, you can't change it.

00:23:03.510 --> 00:23:10.810 align:middle line:90%


00:23:10.810 --> 00:23:12.170 align:middle line:90%
Cultivate some mindfulness.

00:23:12.170 --> 00:23:13.240 align:middle line:90%
Be present.

00:23:13.240 --> 00:23:15.050 align:middle line:84%
Practice being in
your body, practice

00:23:15.050 --> 00:23:18.640 align:middle line:84%
tasting your food in a
way that is fascinated

00:23:18.640 --> 00:23:21.120 align:middle line:90%
and absorbed and nonjudgmental.

00:23:21.120 --> 00:23:24.190 align:middle line:10%
So mindfulness is about
noticing what you're feeling,

00:23:24.190 --> 00:23:26.490 align:middle line:10%
paying attention,
and not judging it.

00:23:26.490 --> 00:23:28.970 align:middle line:84%
By non-judgemental
the explanation is--

00:23:28.970 --> 00:23:29.800 align:middle line:90%
Don't edit.

00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:33.040 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's got-- you've
got to let it come in.

00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:37.520 align:middle line:10%
So it's an awareness without
the discriminating mind,

00:23:37.520 --> 00:23:39.800 align:middle line:10%
without a mind
that is saying this

00:23:39.800 --> 00:23:42.690 align:middle line:10%
is better than that, comparing
without the comparing mind.

00:23:42.690 --> 00:23:45.090 align:middle line:10%
So it's good to notice
when our mind is wandering

00:23:45.090 --> 00:23:47.730 align:middle line:10%
and be able to take note
of it without judgment,

00:23:47.730 --> 00:23:49.500 align:middle line:10%
and be curious about
what's on the mind,

00:23:49.500 --> 00:23:50.930 align:middle line:10%
and gently bring it back.

00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:54.810 align:middle line:84%
So pay attention with a
curious, receptive perspective,

00:23:54.810 --> 00:23:58.560 align:middle line:84%
allowing you to see new aspects
and angles in everyday events.

00:23:58.560 --> 00:24:01.100 align:middle line:90%


00:24:01.100 --> 00:24:02.340 align:middle line:90%
Close your eyes.

00:24:02.340 --> 00:24:03.220 align:middle line:90%
Mm, why?

00:24:03.220 --> 00:24:04.480 align:middle line:84%
Because I want
to test something.

00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:07.140 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:24:07.140 --> 00:24:08.055 align:middle line:90%
You feel anything?

00:24:08.055 --> 00:24:08.810 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:24:08.810 --> 00:24:10.200 align:middle line:90%
What am I supposed to feel?

00:24:10.200 --> 00:24:11.940 align:middle line:90%
Oh, great.

00:24:11.940 --> 00:24:14.320 align:middle line:90%
Learning what I already knew.

00:24:14.320 --> 00:24:15.120 align:middle line:90%
Oh, really?

00:24:15.120 --> 00:24:16.300 align:middle line:90%
What's-- what's that?

00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:18.930 align:middle line:84%
That you're completely unaware
of everything around you.

00:24:18.930 --> 00:24:20.950 align:middle line:90%
Woo, what makes you so special?

00:24:20.950 --> 00:24:21.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm aware.

00:24:21.690 --> 00:24:22.400 align:middle line:90%
Oh, really?

00:24:22.400 --> 00:24:23.900 align:middle line:84%
Big deal.
-Yeah, really.

00:24:23.900 --> 00:24:25.520 align:middle line:10%
Why don't you test me?
Go ahead.

00:24:25.520 --> 00:24:27.153 align:middle line:84%
-All right, I will test you.
-OK.

00:24:27.153 --> 00:24:27.932 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:24:27.932 --> 00:24:29.720 align:middle line:90%
What am I doing?

00:24:29.720 --> 00:24:31.470 align:middle line:84%
Waving your hands
in front of my face.

00:24:31.470 --> 00:24:33.000 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, because you're
obviously cheating.

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:34.427 align:middle line:84%
I'm not.
I'm not cheating.

00:24:34.427 --> 00:24:35.160 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, you're looking.

00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:36.320 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm not.

00:24:36.320 --> 00:24:39.340 align:middle line:90%
Do something else.

00:24:39.340 --> 00:24:41.960 align:middle line:84%
Four fingers in
front of my face.

00:24:41.960 --> 00:24:43.700 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:24:43.700 --> 00:24:46.062 align:middle line:10%
Mm, three fingers.

00:24:46.062 --> 00:24:47.940 align:middle line:10%
Oh, come on, make it harder.

00:24:47.940 --> 00:24:49.739 align:middle line:10%
Your hands are above my head.
-What?

00:24:49.739 --> 00:24:51.390 align:middle line:10%
How are you doing that?

00:24:51.390 --> 00:24:53.070 align:middle line:90%
Because I'm completely aware.

00:24:53.070 --> 00:24:54.010 align:middle line:90%
Don't you want to be aware?

00:24:54.010 --> 00:24:55.580 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, sure.

00:24:55.580 --> 00:24:58.010 align:middle line:84%
OK, so then start paying
attention to the little things

00:24:58.010 --> 00:25:00.080 align:middle line:90%
around you by being mindful.

00:25:00.080 --> 00:25:01.622 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I'll try.

00:25:01.622 --> 00:25:04.660 align:middle line:84%
-No, there's no try, remember?
-Oh, yeah, right.

00:25:04.660 --> 00:25:06.240 align:middle line:90%
I forgot about that.

00:25:06.240 --> 00:25:08.640 align:middle line:90%
So.

00:25:08.640 --> 00:25:10.770 align:middle line:84%
JEFFREY M. SCHWARTZ (VOICEOVER):
You are not your brain

00:25:10.770 --> 00:25:14.604 align:middle line:90%
means you are not your thought.

00:25:14.604 --> 00:25:17.040 align:middle line:84%
What happens during
mindfulness practice

00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:19.540 align:middle line:84%
is that people are
less likely to be,

00:25:19.540 --> 00:25:24.260 align:middle line:84%
as it were, constantly
stressed, rushed off their feet.

00:25:24.260 --> 00:25:27.140 align:middle line:10%
But also, they're
less likely to respond

00:25:27.140 --> 00:25:28.720 align:middle line:10%
to their own negative thinking.

00:25:28.720 --> 00:25:30.940 align:middle line:84%
But the first step
is to stop and be

00:25:30.940 --> 00:25:34.280 align:middle line:90%
aware of your emotional state.

00:25:34.280 --> 00:25:37.380 align:middle line:84%
And recognizing that
you have thought,

00:25:37.380 --> 00:25:39.670 align:middle line:84%
but you aren't your
thoughts, that you don't have

00:25:39.670 --> 00:25:43.570 align:middle line:84%
to identify with the
voice that's producing

00:25:43.570 --> 00:25:44.710 align:middle line:90%
thoughts in your mind.

00:25:44.710 --> 00:25:47.680 align:middle line:84%
That thought that's coming
in, I mean, that is not you.

00:25:47.680 --> 00:25:51.760 align:middle line:84%
That's a production of your
habits, of your experience,

00:25:51.760 --> 00:25:54.030 align:middle line:84%
but it's a commentary
on your experience.

00:25:54.030 --> 00:25:55.480 align:middle line:90%
It isn't your experience.

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:57.687 align:middle line:84%
It's like mistaking
the menu for the meal

00:25:57.687 --> 00:25:58.520 align:middle line:90%
that you're going to eat.

00:25:58.520 --> 00:26:01.710 align:middle line:84%
So your emotional
states are recognized

00:26:01.710 --> 00:26:05.350 align:middle line:84%
as being emotional
states, not who you are.

00:26:05.350 --> 00:26:07.790 align:middle line:84%
And they're always passing,
they're always in flux.

00:26:07.790 --> 00:26:11.750 align:middle line:84%
It's happy, and sad,
and angry, and fearful.

00:26:11.750 --> 00:26:15.540 align:middle line:84%
Mindful awareness is like
this vast sky, where problems

00:26:15.540 --> 00:26:17.780 align:middle line:84%
and concerns and issues are
like these little passing

00:26:17.780 --> 00:26:23.060 align:middle line:84%
clouds or thoughts that
just pass through your mind.

00:26:23.060 --> 00:26:23.913 align:middle line:90%
Look at that thought.

00:26:23.913 --> 00:26:25.302 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you mean my thought?

00:26:25.302 --> 00:26:26.230 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:26:26.230 --> 00:26:28.520 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that's from last night.

00:26:28.520 --> 00:26:29.560 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:26:29.560 --> 00:26:31.990 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that's actually--
I was mad last night,

00:26:31.990 --> 00:26:34.250 align:middle line:84%
so that's like one
angry little thought.

00:26:34.250 --> 00:26:35.060 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I know.

00:26:35.060 --> 00:26:37.190 align:middle line:84%
But don't judge it.
Just look at it.

00:26:37.190 --> 00:26:38.510 align:middle line:90%
But why?

00:26:38.510 --> 00:26:39.880 align:middle line:84%
Because when you
judge your thoughts,

00:26:39.880 --> 00:26:42.322 align:middle line:84%
then you're engaging in it,
and then it just upsets you.

00:26:42.322 --> 00:26:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I actually
got pretty upset,

00:26:43.680 --> 00:26:45.410 align:middle line:90%
like watching my thoughts.

00:26:45.410 --> 00:26:46.730 align:middle line:90%
Well, don't be upset, OK?

00:26:46.730 --> 00:26:48.660 align:middle line:90%
Let me explain this to you.

00:26:48.660 --> 00:26:50.690 align:middle line:84%
Like, if my hand
is the thought, OK?

00:26:50.690 --> 00:26:51.390 align:middle line:90%
Mhm.

00:26:51.390 --> 00:26:54.010 align:middle line:84%
The space in between
is the awareness.

00:26:54.010 --> 00:26:58.250 align:middle line:84%
Don't focus on my hand,
focus on the awareness.

00:26:58.250 --> 00:26:59.170 align:middle line:90%
You see?

00:26:59.170 --> 00:27:02.920 align:middle line:84%
When you're mindful of
it, then you feel better.

00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:05.221 align:middle line:84%
Wow, that's actually
pretty awesome.

00:27:05.221 --> 00:27:05.920 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:27:05.920 --> 00:27:08.420 align:middle line:10%
You know, like when
you're mindless,

00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:10.390 align:middle line:10%
then your brain
doesn't understand it.

00:27:10.390 --> 00:27:12.570 align:middle line:10%
But if you're mindful,
your brain gets it.

00:27:12.570 --> 00:27:13.840 align:middle line:10%
You just need to
change your brain.

00:27:13.840 --> 00:27:15.570 align:middle line:10%
Well, what's wrong
with the one I have?

00:27:15.570 --> 00:27:16.600 align:middle line:10%
Where do I start?

00:27:16.600 --> 00:27:18.271 align:middle line:10%
Well, yeah, that's real funny.

00:27:18.271 --> 00:27:19.670 align:middle line:10%
Well, at least you're
starting to get it.

00:27:19.670 --> 00:27:23.590 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, I mean, I am.

00:27:23.590 --> 00:27:26.810 align:middle line:84%
So mindfulness can get you
out of these reactive loops

00:27:26.810 --> 00:27:30.020 align:middle line:84%
and change the
structure of your brain.

