00:27:53.411 --> 00:27:54.110 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:27:54.110 --> 00:27:57.360 align:middle line:84%
You can choose to get in
touch with this idea of choice,

00:27:57.360 --> 00:27:58.640 align:middle line:90%
what I call a choice point.

00:27:58.640 --> 00:28:00.350 align:middle line:84%
You can choose what
you want to do with it.

00:28:00.350 --> 00:28:02.290 align:middle line:84%
How do you want
to relate to life?

00:28:02.290 --> 00:28:03.560 align:middle line:84%
You're not-- you
don't need to be

00:28:03.560 --> 00:28:06.790 align:middle line:84%
enslaved by the automatic
reactions that are there.

00:28:06.790 --> 00:28:09.810 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness tries to get
control of it, but it's hard.

00:28:09.810 --> 00:28:13.470 align:middle line:84%
And basically what we have to do
is we observe ourselves acting

00:28:13.470 --> 00:28:15.660 align:middle line:84%
in a certain way,
and then we try

00:28:15.660 --> 00:28:20.300 align:middle line:84%
to put in checks and balances
in our brains that let us cope

00:28:20.300 --> 00:28:22.730 align:middle line:84%
with those reactions
when they are occurring,

00:28:22.730 --> 00:28:25.760 align:middle line:84%
rather than preventing them from
occurring in the first place.

00:28:25.760 --> 00:28:27.720 align:middle line:84%
That's the hard part,
preventing them from occurring.

00:28:27.720 --> 00:28:34.790 align:middle line:10%
You are choosing to shift
your center of identification

00:28:34.790 --> 00:28:37.150 align:middle line:10%
from the stream to the watcher.

00:28:37.150 --> 00:28:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And mindfulness can give you
better control over your--

00:28:42.180 --> 00:28:44.410 align:middle line:84%
not only your cortex, but
your ability of your cortex

00:28:44.410 --> 00:28:47.170 align:middle line:84%
to control the other
parts of your brain.

00:28:47.170 --> 00:28:50.640 align:middle line:84%
Why would one choose
self-limitation when you

00:28:50.640 --> 00:28:53.027 align:middle line:90%
can be more free, more open?

00:28:53.027 --> 00:28:55.829 align:middle line:90%


00:28:55.829 --> 00:28:56.763 align:middle line:10%
Wait a minute.

00:28:56.763 --> 00:28:57.680 align:middle line:10%
What are you doing?

00:28:57.680 --> 00:28:59.320 align:middle line:10%
Well, I'm calling you out.

00:28:59.320 --> 00:29:00.770 align:middle line:10%
Calling me out?

00:29:00.770 --> 00:29:03.960 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, I'm sick of you thinking
you're so much better than me.

00:29:03.960 --> 00:29:05.900 align:middle line:10%
Mindfulness this isn't
about being better.

00:29:05.900 --> 00:29:09.132 align:middle line:10%
Oh, there you go again with
that little mindfulness talk.

00:29:09.132 --> 00:29:11.060 align:middle line:84%
All right, if this
is how you want it,

00:29:11.060 --> 00:29:12.175 align:middle line:90%
then I'm going to show you.

00:29:12.175 --> 00:29:13.715 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I'm calling you out.

00:29:13.715 --> 00:29:17.285 align:middle line:90%


00:29:17.285 --> 00:29:19.110 align:middle line:10%
It didn't have to be
this way, you know.

00:29:19.110 --> 00:29:20.960 align:middle line:84%
If you stopped thinking
you were better than me,

00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:22.500 align:middle line:90%
I wouldn't even have to do this.

00:29:22.500 --> 00:29:23.830 align:middle line:90%
Don't you get it?

00:29:23.830 --> 00:29:26.450 align:middle line:84%
You have them both,
mindful and mindless.

00:29:26.450 --> 00:29:27.940 align:middle line:10%
It's part of the same coin.

00:29:27.940 --> 00:29:30.080 align:middle line:10%
I'm saying you've got
both side of the coin.

00:29:30.080 --> 00:29:31.660 align:middle line:10%
What's all this coin talk?

00:29:31.660 --> 00:29:35.396 align:middle line:10%
I'm saying you get to choose
which one you use-- be mindful

00:29:35.396 --> 00:29:36.520 align:middle line:10%
or being mindless.

00:29:36.520 --> 00:29:38.210 align:middle line:10%
You have both parts to you.

00:29:38.210 --> 00:29:40.000 align:middle line:10%
But I thought I always
had to be mindful.

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:41.810 align:middle line:10%
MINDFUL: Not at all.

00:29:41.810 --> 00:29:44.290 align:middle line:10%
Look, every day, when
you're doing your routine,

00:29:44.290 --> 00:29:47.060 align:middle line:10%
you're using the mindless side
because you're used to it.

00:29:47.060 --> 00:29:49.710 align:middle line:10%
It's a routine, so you just
go through the motions.

00:29:49.710 --> 00:29:52.050 align:middle line:10%
But what happens is,
over time, you tend

00:29:52.050 --> 00:29:53.520 align:middle line:10%
to do that for your whole life.

00:29:53.520 --> 00:29:56.950 align:middle line:10%
So you need to be mindful
of other parts of your life,

00:29:56.950 --> 00:29:59.520 align:middle line:10%
so that you're not
mindless all the time.

00:29:59.520 --> 00:30:02.310 align:middle line:10%
So does this mean I
can't call you out?

00:30:02.310 --> 00:30:03.480 align:middle line:10%
No.

00:30:03.480 --> 00:30:05.780 align:middle line:10%
But if you really want to,
we'll do it this one time

00:30:05.780 --> 00:30:07.780 align:middle line:10%
and it can be our
mindless moment together.

00:30:07.780 --> 00:30:09.830 align:middle line:10%
All right.
Are you ready?

00:30:09.830 --> 00:30:10.740 align:middle line:10%
Are you ready?

00:30:10.740 --> 00:30:11.740 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, I'm ready.

00:30:11.740 --> 00:30:12.750 align:middle line:10%
All right, bring it.

00:30:12.750 --> 00:30:20.850 align:middle line:90%


00:30:20.850 --> 00:30:21.746 align:middle line:90%
Ow.

00:30:21.746 --> 00:30:26.180 align:middle line:10%
Man, I'm hit, and you-- you
didn't even draw your gun.

00:30:26.180 --> 00:30:28.170 align:middle line:10%
You didn't even get hit.

00:30:28.170 --> 00:30:29.651 align:middle line:10%
You're not even
paying attention.

00:30:29.651 --> 00:30:30.350 align:middle line:10%
See?

00:30:30.350 --> 00:30:33.270 align:middle line:10%
When you're mindful, you'll
start realizing these things.

00:30:33.270 --> 00:30:35.614 align:middle line:10%
So start practicing.

00:30:35.614 --> 00:30:38.480 align:middle line:90%
I'll practice just for you.

00:30:38.480 --> 00:30:40.350 align:middle line:84%
ELLEN LANGER (VOICEOVER):
Mindfulness, as I study it,

00:30:40.350 --> 00:30:45.630 align:middle line:84%
it's the very simple process
of noticing new things.

00:30:45.630 --> 00:30:48.290 align:middle line:10%
And as you notice new things,
several things happen.

00:30:48.290 --> 00:30:51.140 align:middle line:10%
The first is that you come
to see you didn't know it

00:30:51.140 --> 00:30:52.590 align:middle line:10%
as well as you thought you did.

00:30:52.590 --> 00:30:55.010 align:middle line:84%
It's like pulling back the
curtain on the "Wizard of Oz,"

00:30:55.010 --> 00:30:56.200 align:middle line:90%
and we see what's really.

00:30:56.200 --> 00:31:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And this act of noticing is
the essence of engagement.

00:31:00.470 --> 00:31:02.460 align:middle line:10%
It just opens
you up to becoming

00:31:02.460 --> 00:31:05.590 align:middle line:10%
aware of things that
were there before

00:31:05.590 --> 00:31:07.140 align:middle line:10%
but were not in awareness.

00:31:07.140 --> 00:31:08.880 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
what you notice.

00:31:08.880 --> 00:31:12.410 align:middle line:84%
The things you notice can be
silly, but just the noticing

00:31:12.410 --> 00:31:14.430 align:middle line:84%
breaks down the
boundary between you

00:31:14.430 --> 00:31:15.965 align:middle line:90%
and that which is being noticed.

00:31:15.965 --> 00:31:19.600 align:middle line:84%
So now, everything that's old
becomes new again, in some

00:31:19.600 --> 00:31:21.650 align:middle line:84%
sense, and becomes
naturally interesting.

00:31:21.650 --> 00:31:24.040 align:middle line:84%
And life becomes
a bit less serious

00:31:24.040 --> 00:31:26.700 align:middle line:84%
and we become-- we take
ourselves less seriously.

00:31:26.700 --> 00:31:30.430 align:middle line:84%
So you're more energetic when
you're doing this, not less so.

00:31:30.430 --> 00:31:31.810 align:middle line:90%
The neurons are firing.

00:31:31.810 --> 00:31:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And in the earliest work we
did, when we taught people

00:31:34.900 --> 00:31:37.100 align:middle line:84%
to be mindful in
nursing homes, we

00:31:37.100 --> 00:31:38.600 align:middle line:90%
found that they lived longer.

00:31:38.600 --> 00:31:42.690 align:middle line:84%
So really, our only choice
is are we paying attention

00:31:42.690 --> 00:31:43.425 align:middle line:90%
or are we not.

00:31:43.425 --> 00:31:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And in even at that,
some people will pay

00:31:46.090 --> 00:31:49.430 align:middle line:90%
attention better than others.

00:31:49.430 --> 00:31:50.400 align:middle line:90%
What do you think?

00:31:50.400 --> 00:31:52.090 align:middle line:90%
About what?

00:31:52.090 --> 00:31:52.890 align:middle line:90%
Look.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:53.590 align:middle line:90%
Well, I'm looking.

00:31:53.590 --> 00:31:55.199 align:middle line:84%
I'm looking.
What?

00:31:55.199 --> 00:31:56.060 align:middle line:90%
Are you blind?

00:31:56.060 --> 00:31:57.410 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:31:57.410 --> 00:31:58.910 align:middle line:90%
Look at it.

00:31:58.910 --> 00:32:01.110 align:middle line:90%
What am I supposed to see?

00:32:01.110 --> 00:32:02.930 align:middle line:90%
My new hair.

00:32:02.930 --> 00:32:03.920 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:32:03.920 --> 00:32:04.770 align:middle line:90%
Duh.

00:32:04.770 --> 00:32:06.010 align:middle line:90%
That's new hair.

00:32:06.010 --> 00:32:09.631 align:middle line:84%
You're just being mindless
again, not noticing new things.

00:32:09.631 --> 00:32:11.830 align:middle line:84%
Oh, you know what?
Well, whoop-dee-doo, OK?

00:32:11.830 --> 00:32:13.150 align:middle line:90%
So I don't notice things.

00:32:13.150 --> 00:32:15.780 align:middle line:84%
Well, you need to be more
mindful so you can notice

00:32:15.780 --> 00:32:18.490 align:middle line:84%
new things and pay
attention, therefore,

00:32:18.490 --> 00:32:20.210 align:middle line:90%
paying better attention to me.

00:32:20.210 --> 00:32:21.710 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK, yeah, I got it.

00:32:21.710 --> 00:32:22.520 align:middle line:90%
Do you get it?

00:32:22.520 --> 00:32:23.438 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I got it.

00:32:23.438 --> 00:32:24.138 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:32:24.138 --> 00:32:34.440 align:middle line:90%


00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:38.190 align:middle line:10%
We're beginning to drill down
through mindfulness practice

00:32:38.190 --> 00:32:40.920 align:middle line:10%
into the core question
of psychology,

00:32:40.920 --> 00:32:42.920 align:middle line:10%
like who the hell are we
in the first place, what

00:32:42.920 --> 00:32:44.840 align:middle line:10%
does it-- what is the self?

00:32:44.840 --> 00:32:47.690 align:middle line:84%
That's what the study of
psychology is all about.

00:32:47.690 --> 00:32:51.950 align:middle line:84%
The term ego gets a bad rep,
but it was meant neutral.

00:32:51.950 --> 00:32:55.940 align:middle line:84%
By Freud, for example, he drew
on the original Latin and Greek

00:32:55.940 --> 00:32:58.160 align:middle line:84%
roots to use the
word ego meaning Ich,

00:32:58.160 --> 00:33:01.310 align:middle line:84%
or I. It simply is a
self-identification.

00:33:01.310 --> 00:33:05.820 align:middle line:10%
It's ego, whether it's a hyper
inflated-- the best person--

00:33:05.820 --> 00:33:08.110 align:middle line:10%
best speaker in the world,
or I'm the worst in the world

00:33:08.110 --> 00:33:09.440 align:middle line:10%
and people aren't
going to like me.

00:33:09.440 --> 00:33:10.840 align:middle line:90%
Both of those are ego driven.

00:33:10.840 --> 00:33:12.620 align:middle line:84%
When someone says
you have a huge ego,

00:33:12.620 --> 00:33:14.690 align:middle line:84%
that's not normally
considered a compliment.

00:33:14.690 --> 00:33:18.470 align:middle line:10%
An individual person's
identity, that's not a problem.

00:33:18.470 --> 00:33:22.040 align:middle line:10%
Egotism, concern about
one's self and concern

00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:25.210 align:middle line:10%
about how the outcome
of your performance

00:33:25.210 --> 00:33:27.770 align:middle line:10%
is going to reflect on your
feelings about yourself

00:33:27.770 --> 00:33:29.690 align:middle line:10%
and what other people
will think of you,

00:33:29.690 --> 00:33:32.990 align:middle line:10%
all of that complication,
that is what gets in the way.

00:33:32.990 --> 00:33:35.610 align:middle line:10%
But I think we
have the possibility

00:33:35.610 --> 00:33:38.970 align:middle line:10%
to evolve culturally
to understand

00:33:38.970 --> 00:33:41.850 align:middle line:10%
the neurobiology
of a separate cell

00:33:41.850 --> 00:33:44.190 align:middle line:10%
and how it is in
fact a delusion.

00:33:44.190 --> 00:33:46.855 align:middle line:84%
So the conscious
self is not in charge.

00:33:46.855 --> 00:33:48.110 align:middle line:90%
It's here to learn.

00:33:48.110 --> 00:33:50.310 align:middle line:84%
That's the function
of the ego, to learn

00:33:50.310 --> 00:33:51.830 align:middle line:90%
what we need for this lifetime.

00:33:51.830 --> 00:33:55.270 align:middle line:84%
So much in modern culture
promotes competition

00:33:55.270 --> 00:33:57.300 align:middle line:90%
and a sense of self as separate.

00:33:57.300 --> 00:34:01.090 align:middle line:84%
These are culturally
learned delusions.

00:34:01.090 --> 00:34:03.250 align:middle line:84%
And sadly, they're
not only making

00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:05.450 align:middle line:84%
people have
meaningless lives and

00:34:05.450 --> 00:34:09.449 align:middle line:84%
unhealthy physiological states,
but it's destroying our planet.

00:34:09.449 --> 00:34:14.530 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness is an invitation to
actually experience in reality

00:34:14.530 --> 00:34:16.320 align:middle line:90%
how interconnected we are.

00:34:16.320 --> 00:34:19.440 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to get joy
from your accomplishments.

00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:21.929 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's the kind of
world we need to push for.

00:34:21.929 --> 00:34:26.659 align:middle line:84%
To give you an example, people
that are in institutions where

00:34:26.659 --> 00:34:29.920 align:middle line:84%
they're chronically depressed,
if you listen to them as they

00:34:29.920 --> 00:34:33.239 align:middle line:84%
talk, every third word is
I. I'm not feeling this,

00:34:33.239 --> 00:34:34.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm feeling-- I'm
feeling terrible.

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:37.290 align:middle line:10%
I-- I did-- I'm guilty,
I'm bad, I did this,

00:34:37.290 --> 00:34:41.710 align:middle line:10%
I did that, I, I, I, I, I, I,
I. I is like the color white.

00:34:41.710 --> 00:34:42.510 align:middle line:10%
It has no color.

00:34:42.510 --> 00:34:48.350 align:middle line:10%
You color it red, blue, green
with a feeling that represents

00:34:48.350 --> 00:34:52.840 align:middle line:10%
the personality that you feel
is the correct personality

00:34:52.840 --> 00:34:54.290 align:middle line:10%
for that action.

00:34:54.290 --> 00:34:56.260 align:middle line:84%
And you may have gotten
this from observing

00:34:56.260 --> 00:34:58.160 align:middle line:84%
your parents or other
parental figures

00:34:58.160 --> 00:35:03.820 align:middle line:84%
or friends or whatever who
adapt similar types of colorings

00:35:03.820 --> 00:35:06.460 align:middle line:84%
to their I word
when they're having

00:35:06.460 --> 00:35:10.660 align:middle line:84%
a certain emotional
response to a situation.

00:35:10.660 --> 00:35:15.725 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness is the ability
to go to color white.

00:35:15.725 --> 00:35:27.605 align:middle line:90%


00:35:27.605 --> 00:35:29.650 align:middle line:84%
Um, I think I, like,
want you to teach me how

00:35:29.650 --> 00:35:31.180 align:middle line:90%
to become, like, more mindful.

00:35:31.180 --> 00:35:33.020 align:middle line:90%
Oh, great.

00:35:33.020 --> 00:35:34.690 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, because,
like, the other day,

00:35:34.690 --> 00:35:37.170 align:middle line:84%
I just had, like,
this little incident,

00:35:37.170 --> 00:35:39.150 align:middle line:90%
where I wasn't mindful.

00:35:39.150 --> 00:35:40.000 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:35:40.000 --> 00:35:41.540 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's kind
of a long story,

00:35:41.540 --> 00:35:44.825 align:middle line:84%
but basically, like, I was
just on my phone, like texting,

00:35:44.825 --> 00:35:46.400 align:middle line:84%
and I was just
crossing the street.

00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:48.190 align:middle line:84%
And the next thing I knew,
like, this big bus showed

00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:49.930 align:middle line:90%
up and almost ran me over.

00:35:49.930 --> 00:35:51.541 align:middle line:84%
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:35:51.541 --> 00:35:53.170 align:middle line:84%
-Uh, yeah.
-Almost died.

00:35:53.170 --> 00:35:55.221 align:middle line:84%
You're gonna get
yourself killed, dude.

00:35:55.221 --> 00:35:55.920 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:35:55.920 --> 00:35:58.910 align:middle line:84%
That's why-- that's why I turned
to you to become more mindful.

00:35:58.910 --> 00:36:00.090 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:36:00.090 --> 00:36:02.300 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think you're
already being more mindful.

00:36:02.300 --> 00:36:03.744 align:middle line:84%
This is a step in
the right direction.

00:36:03.744 --> 00:36:05.190 align:middle line:84%
Right.
I see it.

00:36:05.190 --> 00:36:06.090 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Let me show you.

00:36:06.090 --> 00:36:10.900 align:middle line:84%
This is-- this is you
with mindlessness, OK?

00:36:10.900 --> 00:36:12.770 align:middle line:84%
This is your space,
the awareness,

00:36:12.770 --> 00:36:14.710 align:middle line:84%
this tiny little space.
-OK.

00:36:14.710 --> 00:36:17.651 align:middle line:84%
This is your awareness
with mindfulness.

00:36:17.651 --> 00:36:19.080 align:middle line:84%
-Right.
-OK?

00:36:19.080 --> 00:36:20.690 align:middle line:90%
Mindlessness.

00:36:20.690 --> 00:36:22.450 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness.
-Mhm.

00:36:22.450 --> 00:36:24.130 align:middle line:90%
Mindlessness.

00:36:24.130 --> 00:36:25.080 align:middle line:90%
Mindfulness.

00:36:25.080 --> 00:36:28.060 align:middle line:84%
You see how you have
more awareness to learn

00:36:28.060 --> 00:36:29.210 align:middle line:90%
about your surroundings.

00:36:29.210 --> 00:36:30.990 align:middle line:90%
You end up seeing a bus.

00:36:30.990 --> 00:36:31.690 align:middle line:90%
Otherwise--

00:36:31.690 --> 00:36:33.090 align:middle line:90%
[TIRES SCREECHING]

00:36:33.090 --> 00:36:34.706 align:middle line:84%
Mindlessness.
-Wow.

00:36:34.706 --> 00:36:36.620 align:middle line:10%
That bus would
have ran you over.

00:36:36.620 --> 00:36:38.149 align:middle line:84%
-Oh, yeah.
-OK?

00:36:38.149 --> 00:36:39.271 align:middle line:84%
You get it?
Got it?

00:36:39.271 --> 00:36:41.880 align:middle line:84%
Good?
-Yes, I get it, got it, good.

00:36:41.880 --> 00:36:43.470 align:middle line:84%
Get it, got it, good.
-All right.

