00:37:02.080 --> 00:37:04.215 align:middle line:10%
illness, whether you're
talking about pain

00:37:04.215 --> 00:37:09.430 align:middle line:10%
or whether you're talking about
any kind of debilitating state,

00:37:09.430 --> 00:37:13.250 align:middle line:10%
fatigue, what makes it
worse is how we process

00:37:13.250 --> 00:37:15.110 align:middle line:10%
it centrally in our brain.

00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:16.730 align:middle line:84%
So I feel myself
getting anxious.

00:37:16.730 --> 00:37:19.590 align:middle line:84%
One of those unconscious
systems has been triggered.

00:37:19.590 --> 00:37:23.850 align:middle line:84%
So you now say, OK, I can't
stop it, so what can I do.

00:37:23.850 --> 00:37:25.720 align:middle line:90%
I can breathe.

00:37:25.720 --> 00:37:26.960 align:middle line:90%
Take in the air.

00:37:26.960 --> 00:37:30.900 align:middle line:84%
That trick kicks on the
parasympathetic nervous system,

00:37:30.900 --> 00:37:33.200 align:middle line:84%
which counteracts the
sympathetic, which is the fight

00:37:33.200 --> 00:37:36.700 align:middle line:84%
flight system, and kind of slows
everything down a little bit.

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:38.950 align:middle line:10%
And so when we change
the system that's here,

00:37:38.950 --> 00:37:42.020 align:middle line:10%
the stress cycle between
our thoughts that come up,

00:37:42.020 --> 00:37:44.190 align:middle line:10%
so our thoughts-- an event
happens and we immediately

00:37:44.190 --> 00:37:47.570 align:middle line:10%
perceive something as scary or
we need to do something about,

00:37:47.570 --> 00:37:50.040 align:middle line:10%
something that's urgent
or it's important,

00:37:50.040 --> 00:37:52.350 align:middle line:10%
our brain creates a snap
judgment of it being good,

00:37:52.350 --> 00:37:54.510 align:middle line:10%
bad, right, wrong,
fair, or unfair,

00:37:54.510 --> 00:37:56.090 align:middle line:10%
and goes into a reactive mode.

00:37:56.090 --> 00:37:59.880 align:middle line:84%
As the great stress
researcher Hans Selye put it,

00:37:59.880 --> 00:38:03.710 align:middle line:84%
"It's not stress that kills us,
it's our reaction to stress."

00:38:03.710 --> 00:38:05.990 align:middle line:84%
Stress is a function
not of events,

00:38:05.990 --> 00:38:07.970 align:middle line:84%
but the view you
take of the event.

00:38:07.970 --> 00:38:10.340 align:middle line:84%
If you open up that
view in multiple ways,

00:38:10.340 --> 00:38:11.650 align:middle line:90%
it becomes less stressful.

00:38:11.650 --> 00:38:15.390 align:middle line:84%
What we can help is how
we respond to stress.

00:38:15.390 --> 00:38:17.180 align:middle line:84%
That's why breathing
works so well.

00:38:17.180 --> 00:38:21.200 align:middle line:84%
Because it-- it reduces
the stress in the brain.

00:38:21.200 --> 00:38:24.880 align:middle line:84%
It reduces the drive from
the sympathetic system

00:38:24.880 --> 00:38:27.120 align:middle line:84%
that makes you-- that's
releasing adrenaline.

00:38:27.120 --> 00:38:28.870 align:middle line:10%
When you get a
call from somebody

00:38:28.870 --> 00:38:31.440 align:middle line:10%
and you're really stressed out
and you just take the call,

00:38:31.440 --> 00:38:34.844 align:middle line:10%
you're like, yeah, yeah,
yeah, yeah, yeah, OK, OK, OK,

00:38:34.844 --> 00:38:35.770 align:middle line:10%
you know.

00:38:35.770 --> 00:38:37.740 align:middle line:84%
All right, I'll call
you back, you know.

00:38:37.740 --> 00:38:39.940 align:middle line:84%
But if you're calm and
you're not stressed out,

00:38:39.940 --> 00:38:42.410 align:middle line:84%
you take the call and
you take your time.

00:38:42.410 --> 00:38:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And you recognize that
this is important to you

00:38:46.090 --> 00:38:47.110 align:middle line:90%
or to the other person.

00:38:47.110 --> 00:38:48.900 align:middle line:84%
With the less
time for reflection

00:38:48.900 --> 00:38:51.010 align:middle line:84%
that we have nowadays
with so much attention

00:38:51.010 --> 00:38:53.700 align:middle line:84%
to technology filling
the spaces of our day,

00:38:53.700 --> 00:38:55.650 align:middle line:84%
we don't really have a lot
of time for reflection.

00:38:55.650 --> 00:38:57.855 align:middle line:84%
Can you give yourself
three minutes?

00:38:57.855 --> 00:38:59.480 align:middle line:84%
Do you care enough
about yourself

00:38:59.480 --> 00:39:01.780 align:middle line:84%
to give yourself three minutes,
maybe minute in the morning,

00:39:01.780 --> 00:39:04.090 align:middle line:84%
then in the afternoon, minute
in the evening to just sit

00:39:04.090 --> 00:39:05.970 align:middle line:90%
and be present with your breath.

00:39:05.970 --> 00:39:08.750 align:middle line:84%
If we believe we can do
it, we're going to be more

00:39:08.750 --> 00:39:10.457 align:middle line:90%
motivated to actually do it.

00:39:10.457 --> 00:39:11.790 align:middle line:84%
If we don't believe
we can do something,

00:39:11.790 --> 00:39:13.260 align:middle line:84%
we're not going
to actually do it.

00:39:13.260 --> 00:39:15.470 align:middle line:84%
The things we
can't do right now,

00:39:15.470 --> 00:39:17.940 align:middle line:90%
we can learn to do tomorrow.

00:39:17.940 --> 00:39:20.040 align:middle line:84%
When we realize that
there's no outcome

00:39:20.040 --> 00:39:24.950 align:middle line:84%
we must have, that all of
this leads us just to be more

00:39:24.950 --> 00:39:28.897 align:middle line:84%
at peace, easier, less
reason for us to need to hit

00:39:28.897 --> 00:39:29.830 align:middle line:90%
somebody else over the head.

00:39:29.830 --> 00:39:34.770 align:middle line:10%
And mindfulness actually
reduces the risk of depression

00:39:34.770 --> 00:39:38.700 align:middle line:10%
by half in people who are the
most current depressed people,

00:39:38.700 --> 00:39:42.200 align:middle line:10%
with three or more episodes,
that many other treatments have

00:39:42.200 --> 00:39:43.500 align:middle line:10%
failed to treat.

00:39:43.500 --> 00:39:45.870 align:middle line:84%
We also know that it's as
good as antidepressants

00:39:45.870 --> 00:39:46.880 align:middle line:90%
in doing that.

00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:49.120 align:middle line:84%
Now, one thing that we
didn't know eight years ago

00:39:49.120 --> 00:39:50.660 align:middle line:90%
is is that repeatable.

00:39:50.660 --> 00:39:53.380 align:middle line:10%
And we found it is
repeatable, both in our lab

00:39:53.380 --> 00:39:57.470 align:middle line:10%
and in labs around the world,
in lots of different countries,

00:39:57.470 --> 00:39:59.160 align:middle line:10%
have found the same result.

00:39:59.160 --> 00:40:03.370 align:middle line:84%
The simple shift of perspective
can change your relationship

00:40:03.370 --> 00:40:06.660 align:middle line:84%
to the problem when you
take a second look at it

00:40:06.660 --> 00:40:08.880 align:middle line:90%
with a mindful manner.

00:40:08.880 --> 00:40:11.140 align:middle line:84%
Oh, man, what's
happening to me?

00:40:11.140 --> 00:40:12.490 align:middle line:90%
You're out of focus.

00:40:12.490 --> 00:40:13.700 align:middle line:90%
What the heck?

00:40:13.700 --> 00:40:15.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, maybe if you were
a little more mindful,

00:40:15.750 --> 00:40:17.600 align:middle line:90%
these things wouldn't happen.

00:40:17.600 --> 00:40:19.450 align:middle line:90%
Uh, what should I do?

00:40:19.450 --> 00:40:20.725 align:middle line:10%
Try some finger tracing.

00:40:20.725 --> 00:40:22.880 align:middle line:10%
What the-- what the
heck's finger tracing?

00:40:22.880 --> 00:40:24.336 align:middle line:10%
OK, watch me.
Watch me, OK?

00:40:24.336 --> 00:40:25.035 align:middle line:90%
MINDLESS: OK.

00:40:25.035 --> 00:40:26.455 align:middle line:84%
Now you're going
to take your finger

00:40:26.455 --> 00:40:33.800 align:middle line:84%
and very slowly go like this
and see each nook and cranny.

00:40:33.800 --> 00:40:34.500 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:40:34.500 --> 00:40:36.440 align:middle line:90%
Focus very slowly.

00:40:36.440 --> 00:40:38.100 align:middle line:90%
So you mean like this?

00:40:38.100 --> 00:40:40.060 align:middle line:84%
No, no, no, no, that's
too fast and mindless.

00:40:40.060 --> 00:40:42.220 align:middle line:84%
You're not going
to focus like that.

00:40:42.220 --> 00:40:44.520 align:middle line:90%
OK, very slowly.

00:40:44.520 --> 00:40:45.960 align:middle line:90%
Watch it.

00:40:45.960 --> 00:40:49.410 align:middle line:90%
Oh, so you mean slow like this.

00:40:49.410 --> 00:40:50.400 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:40:50.400 --> 00:40:51.920 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:40:51.920 --> 00:40:53.120 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:40:53.120 --> 00:40:54.700 align:middle line:90%
I really like this.

00:40:54.700 --> 00:40:57.270 align:middle line:84%
Like, I'm getting into
the groove of it, like--

00:40:57.270 --> 00:40:59.480 align:middle line:90%
Keep focusing, not bad.

00:40:59.480 --> 00:41:01.155 align:middle line:90%
I can feel a difference.

00:41:01.155 --> 00:41:03.220 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, see, it's not so hard.

00:41:03.220 --> 00:41:06.660 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, this is like--
this is very nice.

00:41:06.660 --> 00:41:10.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to go home and
just get busy finger tracing.

00:41:10.730 --> 00:41:21.140 align:middle line:90%


00:41:21.140 --> 00:41:23.560 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness enables you
to get value for money

00:41:23.560 --> 00:41:25.030 align:middle line:90%
out of your food, right?

00:41:25.030 --> 00:41:26.240 align:middle line:90%
You taste it.

00:41:26.240 --> 00:41:27.740 align:middle line:90%
You're more present.

00:41:27.740 --> 00:41:30.390 align:middle line:10%
Oh, mindless eating brought me
into mindful eating, actually.

00:41:30.390 --> 00:41:33.040 align:middle line:10%
I had a-- I never met a box
of cookies I didn't like.

00:41:33.040 --> 00:41:35.250 align:middle line:84%
Instead of eating
absent-mindedly,

00:41:35.250 --> 00:41:38.660 align:middle line:84%
you know, going to a
restaurant, spend 25 pounds

00:41:38.660 --> 00:41:42.830 align:middle line:84%
for a filet steak, de-da, de-da,
de-da, and then not noticing

00:41:42.830 --> 00:41:44.320 align:middle line:84%
yourself eating
it because you're

00:41:44.320 --> 00:41:46.750 align:middle line:84%
busy having an
earnest conversation

00:41:46.750 --> 00:41:49.750 align:middle line:84%
with your friend about your
relationship with your mother.

00:41:49.750 --> 00:41:51.820 align:middle line:84%
It's like you just
wasted 25 quid.

00:41:51.820 --> 00:41:54.460 align:middle line:84%
And mindful eating
actually helps people

00:41:54.460 --> 00:41:56.290 align:middle line:90%
broaden their view of food.

00:41:56.290 --> 00:41:58.680 align:middle line:84%
So when I crunch into
an apple and somebody

00:41:58.680 --> 00:42:01.820 align:middle line:84%
says why are you making
that loud crunching noise,

00:42:01.820 --> 00:42:05.330 align:middle line:84%
it's bothering me, I think
of my grandmother being

00:42:05.330 --> 00:42:06.900 align:middle line:90%
unable to crunch an apple.

00:42:06.900 --> 00:42:09.300 align:middle line:84%
And I say, wow, I'm just
enjoying every bite.

00:42:09.300 --> 00:42:11.640 align:middle line:84%
Usually, whenever I
eat, whether it's just

00:42:11.640 --> 00:42:14.880 align:middle line:84%
noticing the food, smelling
the food, tasting the food,

00:42:14.880 --> 00:42:17.950 align:middle line:84%
maybe slowing down a little
bit as I'm eating the food,

00:42:17.950 --> 00:42:20.605 align:middle line:84%
what I find is if my
hunger is really high,

00:42:20.605 --> 00:42:22.585 align:middle line:84%
if my hunger is in the
7 to 10 range, which

00:42:22.585 --> 00:42:26.450 align:middle line:84%
is the extreme hunger, and I've
waited and haven't attended

00:42:26.450 --> 00:42:29.910 align:middle line:84%
to my earlier hunger
signals, then I am prone,

00:42:29.910 --> 00:42:32.310 align:middle line:84%
like everybody is, I
think, to mindless eating.

00:42:32.310 --> 00:42:36.650 align:middle line:84%
If we all used our brains in
more energy efficient ways,

00:42:36.650 --> 00:42:38.070 align:middle line:90%
you don't eat as much.

00:42:38.070 --> 00:42:40.450 align:middle line:84%
And you feel much
more energized when

00:42:40.450 --> 00:42:46.580 align:middle line:84%
you don't spend all this
metabolic energy on ego

00:42:46.580 --> 00:42:48.960 align:middle line:90%
related process, on chatter.

00:42:48.960 --> 00:42:52.820 align:middle line:84%
So at a very basic level,
mindfulness enables you

00:42:52.820 --> 00:42:55.970 align:middle line:84%
to kind of, you know,
you taste your experience

00:42:55.970 --> 00:42:57.660 align:middle line:90%
more vividly or more richly.

00:42:57.660 --> 00:43:50.901 align:middle line:90%


00:43:50.901 --> 00:43:52.310 align:middle line:84%
-What?
-How's your food?

00:43:52.310 --> 00:43:53.546 align:middle line:90%
It's good.

00:43:53.546 --> 00:43:55.500 align:middle line:84%
-Hm, you sure?
-Yeah.

00:43:55.500 --> 00:43:56.640 align:middle line:90%
It's all right.

00:43:56.640 --> 00:43:57.840 align:middle line:90%
You're not even tasting it.

00:43:57.840 --> 00:43:58.830 align:middle line:90%
I like it a lot.

00:43:58.830 --> 00:44:00.260 align:middle line:84%
I tasted it.
-No.

00:44:00.260 --> 00:44:04.582 align:middle line:84%
Stop what you're doing and pay
attention to eating your food.

00:44:04.582 --> 00:44:06.570 align:middle line:90%
Well--

00:44:06.570 --> 00:44:07.770 align:middle line:90%
MINDFUL: Take this out.

00:44:07.770 --> 00:44:09.469 align:middle line:84%
OK.
Ow.

00:44:09.469 --> 00:44:11.160 align:middle line:84%
And pay attention to
what you're eating.

00:44:11.160 --> 00:44:12.030 align:middle line:90%
MINDLESS: OK.

00:44:12.030 --> 00:44:14.220 align:middle line:84%
-Chew it slowly.
-I see.

00:44:14.220 --> 00:44:15.800 align:middle line:90%
Really taste it.

00:44:15.800 --> 00:44:17.670 align:middle line:90%
Like this?

00:44:17.670 --> 00:44:19.120 align:middle line:90%
MINDFUL: Slowly eat it.

00:44:19.120 --> 00:44:20.470 align:middle line:90%
Really take it in.

00:44:20.470 --> 00:44:21.260 align:middle line:90%
Mm.

00:44:21.260 --> 00:44:22.030 align:middle line:90%
MINDFUL: OK?

00:44:22.030 --> 00:44:22.730 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:44:22.730 --> 00:44:25.160 align:middle line:84%
Taste it, take it in,
and smell it, you know?

00:44:25.160 --> 00:44:26.520 align:middle line:90%
Really taste it.

00:44:26.520 --> 00:44:30.020 align:middle line:10%
I got to get another
grape to smell it.

00:44:30.020 --> 00:44:31.440 align:middle line:10%
Well, get in there.

00:44:31.440 --> 00:44:33.840 align:middle line:10%
Really get into your food.

00:44:33.840 --> 00:44:35.290 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I smell it.
Smells like

00:44:35.290 --> 00:44:37.011 align:middle line:90%
OK, just take up one bite.

00:44:37.011 --> 00:44:40.240 align:middle line:90%


00:44:40.240 --> 00:44:41.250 align:middle line:90%
So juicy in the middle.

00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:43.115 align:middle line:84%
Do you see the difference
when you're mindful?

00:44:43.115 --> 00:44:43.814 align:middle line:90%
Mm.

00:44:43.814 --> 00:44:45.800 align:middle line:84%
When you're mindful and
you're in the moment?

00:44:45.800 --> 00:44:46.700 align:middle line:90%
Oh, yeah.

00:44:46.700 --> 00:44:48.220 align:middle line:84%
-How much better it is.
-Yeah.

00:44:48.220 --> 00:44:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's like
really delicious.

00:44:50.270 --> 00:44:52.260 align:middle line:84%
MINDFUL: Right, well,
because it's more delicious,

00:44:52.260 --> 00:44:54.190 align:middle line:90%
because you're being mindful.

00:44:54.190 --> 00:44:55.355 align:middle line:90%
That's good stuff.

00:44:55.355 --> 00:45:02.145 align:middle line:90%


00:45:02.145 --> 00:45:05.600 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness has not only become
increasingly popular practice

00:45:05.600 --> 00:45:08.320 align:middle line:84%
in schools around the
world, but the US military

00:45:08.320 --> 00:45:11.360 align:middle line:84%
has begun to incorporate
it into their centers

00:45:11.360 --> 00:45:13.720 align:middle line:84%
in an effort to help
veterans and active duty

00:45:13.720 --> 00:45:15.830 align:middle line:84%
soldiers overcome
some of the issues

00:45:15.830 --> 00:45:18.665 align:middle line:84%
that they deal with, such as
post-traumatic stress disorder,

00:45:18.665 --> 00:45:20.910 align:middle line:90%
or PTSD.

00:45:20.910 --> 00:45:24.440 align:middle line:84%
I recently met with Dr. Jackie
Maury, senior scientist project

00:45:24.440 --> 00:45:28.640 align:middle line:84%
director at USC Institute
for Creative Technologies,

00:45:28.640 --> 00:45:31.590 align:middle line:84%
and Dr. Valerie Rice,
the chief of the Army

00:45:31.590 --> 00:45:33.700 align:middle line:84%
Research Laboratory
Field Element

00:45:33.700 --> 00:45:36.040 align:middle line:90%
at Fort Sam Houston in Texas.

00:45:36.040 --> 00:45:39.960 align:middle line:84%
This is the largest army medical
training facility in the world.

00:45:39.960 --> 00:45:42.320 align:middle line:84%
Let's stay take a look at
how this all came about.

00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:45.080 align:middle line:84%
It was about the same time
that the troops were returning

00:45:45.080 --> 00:45:48.240 align:middle line:84%
from the conflicts overseas
and we were beginning

00:45:48.240 --> 00:45:50.070 align:middle line:84%
to realize there
were some pretty

00:45:50.070 --> 00:45:54.150 align:middle line:84%
big issues with PTSD or other
psychological health issues.

00:45:54.150 --> 00:45:56.190 align:middle line:90%
I was in combat arms.

00:45:56.190 --> 00:45:59.180 align:middle line:90%
I was doing the Vietnam era.

00:45:59.180 --> 00:46:01.910 align:middle line:84%
And they taught you
how to be aggressive.

00:46:01.910 --> 00:46:05.880 align:middle line:84%
You are scanning all
the time and you never

00:46:05.880 --> 00:46:08.520 align:middle line:84%
let anybody know what's
going on with you because you

00:46:08.520 --> 00:46:09.960 align:middle line:90%
lose your essence of surprise.

00:46:09.960 --> 00:46:15.210 align:middle line:90%
I mean, if you hurt, so what?

00:46:15.210 --> 00:46:17.420 align:middle line:90%
Mission is first.

00:46:17.420 --> 00:46:21.140 align:middle line:84%
You don't want people
to think you're weak,

00:46:21.140 --> 00:46:22.430 align:middle line:90%
especially if you're a leader.

00:46:22.430 --> 00:46:25.250 align:middle line:84%
A chain is only as strong
as the weakest link.

00:46:25.250 --> 00:46:28.910 align:middle line:84%
And you didn't want
to be that link.

00:46:28.910 --> 00:46:32.445 align:middle line:84%
Because if you was that
link, you was finished.

00:46:32.445 --> 00:46:36.580 align:middle line:84%
If you were in battle, you've
already got enough enemies.

00:46:36.580 --> 00:46:41.550 align:middle line:84%
I mean, then having your own
emotions to be another one?

00:46:41.550 --> 00:46:44.540 align:middle line:90%
It's just-- it's tougher.

00:46:44.540 --> 00:46:46.900 align:middle line:84%
You just want to do
what you're told to do

00:46:46.900 --> 00:46:50.070 align:middle line:84%
and you don't want to
reach out and ask for help.

00:46:50.070 --> 00:46:51.770 align:middle line:84%
To go-- to go to
behavioral health

00:46:51.770 --> 00:46:55.435 align:middle line:90%
was-- uh, you're not a man.

00:46:55.435 --> 00:46:58.430 align:middle line:90%
You ain't no soldier type thing.

00:46:58.430 --> 00:47:01.900 align:middle line:84%
Any activity with
mental health was

00:47:01.900 --> 00:47:06.330 align:middle line:84%
subject to medical discharge
or disciplinary discharge.

00:47:06.330 --> 00:47:08.610 align:middle line:90%
You just didn't.

00:47:08.610 --> 00:47:09.510 align:middle line:90%
That simple.

00:47:09.510 --> 00:47:11.980 align:middle line:84%
So that prevented
a lot of soldiers,

00:47:11.980 --> 00:47:16.740 align:middle line:84%
especially young soldiers,
from going, getting treatment.

00:47:16.740 --> 00:47:20.530 align:middle line:84%
You just don't bother to tell
people because even not being

00:47:20.530 --> 00:47:24.480 align:middle line:84%
able to keep your personal
life in control-- in control

00:47:24.480 --> 00:47:25.990 align:middle line:90%
is perceived as weakness.

00:47:25.990 --> 00:47:28.110 align:middle line:84%
As time went by and I
got involved with the VA,

00:47:28.110 --> 00:47:30.130 align:middle line:84%
I found out that
it was acceptable,

00:47:30.130 --> 00:47:33.450 align:middle line:84%
but I did it after I
got out of the service

00:47:33.450 --> 00:47:35.985 align:middle line:84%
because it just was not
acceptable at that point

00:47:35.985 --> 00:47:37.060 align:middle line:90%
in time.

00:47:37.060 --> 00:47:38.340 align:middle line:90%
There's still stigma.

00:47:38.340 --> 00:47:41.290 align:middle line:84%
But there's still stigma to go
into behavioral health center.

00:47:41.290 --> 00:47:45.440 align:middle line:84%
And so for those individuals who
simply wouldn't go because it

00:47:45.440 --> 00:47:49.470 align:middle line:84%
is behavioral health, then
we can offer something

00:47:49.470 --> 00:47:51.700 align:middle line:84%
like this that's over
a virtual world, where

00:47:51.700 --> 00:47:55.550 align:middle line:84%
they can be, if they
choose to be, anonymous.

00:47:55.550 --> 00:47:57.670 align:middle line:84%
PAUL HARRISON (VOICEOVER):
Dr. Steven Hickman and Alan

00:47:57.670 --> 00:48:01.630 align:middle line:84%
Goldstein both teach mindfulness
in the form of life mindfulness

00:48:01.630 --> 00:48:04.170 align:middle line:84%
based stress reduction
through the virtual world

00:48:04.170 --> 00:48:05.860 align:middle line:90%
of Second Life to veterans.

00:48:05.860 --> 00:48:07.510 align:middle line:84%
So we were approached,
really out of the blue,

00:48:07.510 --> 00:48:10.490 align:middle line:84%
by the folks at ICT
saying we're looking

00:48:10.490 --> 00:48:12.940 align:middle line:84%
for experts in mindfulness
based stress reduction.

00:48:12.940 --> 00:48:16.130 align:middle line:84%
We got the idea to use
a virtual world as sort

00:48:16.130 --> 00:48:18.850 align:middle line:84%
of a place of
relaxation for veterans

00:48:18.850 --> 00:48:20.490 align:middle line:84%
and we found
experts who are very

00:48:20.490 --> 00:48:21.980 align:middle line:90%
interested in working with us.

00:48:21.980 --> 00:48:24.710 align:middle line:84%
And they told us this
amazing project that they've

00:48:24.710 --> 00:48:27.140 align:middle line:84%
been working for quite
some time in providing

00:48:27.140 --> 00:48:30.370 align:middle line:84%
virtual reality and
virtual world training

00:48:30.370 --> 00:48:32.450 align:middle line:90%
in various military settings.

00:48:32.450 --> 00:48:36.570 align:middle line:84%
And we had done a small
village-- and a rocky village

00:48:36.570 --> 00:48:38.240 align:middle line:84%
as a proof of
concept for something

00:48:38.240 --> 00:48:39.490 align:middle line:90%
else in the virtual world.

00:48:39.490 --> 00:48:44.330 align:middle line:84%
And I took one of those veterans
over to see this village.

00:48:44.330 --> 00:48:46.540 align:middle line:84%
He didn't last 10
seconds in the desert.

00:48:46.540 --> 00:48:48.020 align:middle line:90%
He teleported out.

00:48:48.020 --> 00:48:50.300 align:middle line:90%
He said I can't handle this.

00:48:50.300 --> 00:48:51.710 align:middle line:90%
It's too real.

00:48:51.710 --> 00:48:55.820 align:middle line:84%
So that was the impetus for
doing something that looks

00:48:55.820 --> 00:48:58.280 align:middle line:84%
like a hunting
lodge, a ski lodge,

00:48:58.280 --> 00:49:00.940 align:middle line:84%
something that's very
mountainous and green with lots

00:49:00.940 --> 00:49:01.940 align:middle line:90%
of water.

00:49:01.940 --> 00:49:05.190 align:middle line:84%
And we factor that into
the design of the world

00:49:05.190 --> 00:49:06.240 align:middle line:90%
that we made for them.

00:49:06.240 --> 00:49:08.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, when we first
started this study

00:49:08.030 --> 00:49:10.300 align:middle line:84%
and we had the
computers issued to us,

00:49:10.300 --> 00:49:14.170 align:middle line:84%
it was amazing, and
cool, and exciting.

00:49:14.170 --> 00:49:17.190 align:middle line:84%
And you know, you pick
your own animated body

00:49:17.190 --> 00:49:18.710 align:middle line:84%
and you've got to
learn how to fly

00:49:18.710 --> 00:49:20.180 align:middle line:90%
and they teach us how to walk.

00:49:20.180 --> 00:49:23.510 align:middle line:84%
And that was all
really very exciting.

00:49:23.510 --> 00:49:24.850 align:middle line:84%
And you can choose
different worlds

00:49:24.850 --> 00:49:27.900 align:middle line:84%
to go to, and listen, and
see, and just interact

00:49:27.900 --> 00:49:29.480 align:middle line:90%
online in an amazing way.

00:49:29.480 --> 00:49:31.360 align:middle line:84%
So we're looking
at whether or not

00:49:31.360 --> 00:49:35.080 align:middle line:84%
teaching mindfulness improves
those areas, both for veterans

00:49:35.080 --> 00:49:36.390 align:middle line:90%
and for active duty.

00:49:36.390 --> 00:49:37.980 align:middle line:84%
And you might
need just something

00:49:37.980 --> 00:49:42.620 align:middle line:84%
as simple as learning
mindfulness strategies

00:49:42.620 --> 00:49:43.370 align:middle line:90%
and techniques.

00:49:43.370 --> 00:49:48.090 align:middle line:84%
If we can intervene with some
of this and make a palatable

00:49:48.090 --> 00:49:52.170 align:middle line:84%
activity, something
that is a tool rather

00:49:52.170 --> 00:49:54.520 align:middle line:90%
than something mysterious--

00:49:54.520 --> 00:49:57.410 align:middle line:84%
Which, again,
makes the whole idea

00:49:57.410 --> 00:50:00.620 align:middle line:84%
of being an avatar
kind of attractive,

00:50:00.620 --> 00:50:02.760 align:middle line:84%
plus you can look however
you feel like looking,

00:50:02.760 --> 00:50:04.220 align:middle line:90%
if you want to take time.

00:50:04.220 --> 00:50:06.240 align:middle line:84%
For us, it was this whole
novel idea of something

00:50:06.240 --> 00:50:09.270 align:middle line:84%
that we've been teaching
them really involves face

00:50:09.270 --> 00:50:12.090 align:middle line:84%
to face contact in our
minds, and this idea

00:50:12.090 --> 00:50:14.250 align:middle line:84%
of doing this in a virtual
world where all of us

00:50:14.250 --> 00:50:16.570 align:middle line:84%
is represented by
an avatar provides

00:50:16.570 --> 00:50:17.700 align:middle line:90%
this great opportunity.

00:50:17.700 --> 00:50:20.610 align:middle line:84%
So that we're not actually
physically there in that world.

00:50:20.610 --> 00:50:22.940 align:middle line:84%
There's this being
that we get to create.

00:50:22.940 --> 00:50:25.890 align:middle line:84%
We can dress the way we want,
we can shape the way we want.

00:50:25.890 --> 00:50:29.090 align:middle line:84%
And people who have
perhaps anxiety about being

00:50:29.090 --> 00:50:31.630 align:middle line:84%
in a social setting
can still sort of

00:50:31.630 --> 00:50:33.990 align:middle line:84%
be in a virtual
social setting where

00:50:33.990 --> 00:50:35.900 align:middle line:84%
they're still in the
safety of their own home.

00:50:35.900 --> 00:50:40.790 align:middle line:84%
We would navigate our
avatar online figures

00:50:40.790 --> 00:50:43.160 align:middle line:84%
to the designated
location in a pavilion.

00:50:43.160 --> 00:50:46.200 align:middle line:84%
Our voices would come through
the headsets and the headphones

00:50:46.200 --> 00:50:49.640 align:middle line:84%
and we would just interact
online in a group forum.

00:50:49.640 --> 00:50:51.440 align:middle line:84%
And what's great
about it, for veterans,

00:50:51.440 --> 00:50:53.560 align:middle line:84%
is even if they're
in rural areas,

00:50:53.560 --> 00:50:54.990 align:middle line:90%
they can come together here.

00:50:54.990 --> 00:50:58.050 align:middle line:84%
They don't have to be
able to go to a center.

00:50:58.050 --> 00:51:00.540 align:middle line:84%
People can be physically
anywhere in the world,

00:51:00.540 --> 00:51:03.900 align:middle line:84%
but can still appear in
Second Life in our classroom.

00:51:03.900 --> 00:51:06.560 align:middle line:84%
I think some people were
afraid they might even cry

00:51:06.560 --> 00:51:08.855 align:middle line:84%
and they didn't want to
cry in front of the group.

00:51:08.855 --> 00:51:12.610 align:middle line:84%
But when you're online,
you can cry all you want.

00:51:12.610 --> 00:51:16.344 align:middle line:84%
Participating online,
that was very--

00:51:16.344 --> 00:51:21.530 align:middle line:84%
I found it very,
very good because we

00:51:21.530 --> 00:51:23.450 align:middle line:84%
everybody interacted
with one another.

00:51:23.450 --> 00:51:26.320 align:middle line:84%
And we did share a lot of
information about each other.

00:51:26.320 --> 00:51:32.350 align:middle line:84%
Some of my best moments that
I've learned how to relax

00:51:32.350 --> 00:51:35.920 align:middle line:90%
is because of this course.

00:51:35.920 --> 00:51:41.450 align:middle line:84%
But that class taught
me that I do matter

00:51:41.450 --> 00:51:45.992 align:middle line:84%
and I have to get
myself in order,

00:51:45.992 --> 00:51:48.840 align:middle line:84%
to not only help me,
but help my-- my folks,

00:51:48.840 --> 00:51:50.590 align:middle line:90%
my friend, my family members.

00:51:50.590 --> 00:51:52.510 align:middle line:84%
That does apply to
all walks of life.

00:51:52.510 --> 00:51:55.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, it's not just
from military stressors.

00:51:55.050 --> 00:51:57.730 align:middle line:84%
It's common everyday things
that people are going through.

00:51:57.730 --> 00:52:00.710 align:middle line:84%
No matter what your scenario,
if you want to feel better,

00:52:00.710 --> 00:52:04.780 align:middle line:84%
do better, then don't let
your life pass you by.

00:52:04.780 --> 00:52:05.780 align:middle line:90%
Be a part of your life.

00:52:05.780 --> 00:52:08.970 align:middle line:84%
Slow things down, pay
attention to what's going on.

00:52:08.970 --> 00:52:11.450 align:middle line:84%
The program, it
just actually makes

00:52:11.450 --> 00:52:13.320 align:middle line:90%
you aware of your surroundings.

00:52:13.320 --> 00:52:16.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm enjoying life a lot more,
the simple things in life,

00:52:16.830 --> 00:52:19.520 align:middle line:84%
like, you know, my
chihuahua sleeping

00:52:19.520 --> 00:52:21.950 align:middle line:84%
on my foot, whereas,
before, I might not

00:52:21.950 --> 00:52:25.860 align:middle line:84%
have realized how she
felt or how comforting

00:52:25.860 --> 00:52:28.240 align:middle line:90%
that was for her to be there.

00:52:28.240 --> 00:52:32.000 align:middle line:84%
Now I can kind of be a
little bit more mindful

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:36.470 align:middle line:84%
of the pleasure that she
obtains from me and the pleasure

00:52:36.470 --> 00:52:39.590 align:middle line:84%
that I obtain from
just being around her.

00:52:39.590 --> 00:52:42.750 align:middle line:84%
I really sit back
now just take my time.

00:52:42.750 --> 00:52:46.870 align:middle line:84%
Sit outside, drink some
tea, listen to the wind blow

00:52:46.870 --> 00:52:48.780 align:middle line:84%
through the trees,
listen to the birds,

00:52:48.780 --> 00:52:51.530 align:middle line:84%
count the cars, how many
color cars or whatever,

00:52:51.530 --> 00:52:53.300 align:middle line:84%
like I used to do
when I was a kid.

00:52:53.300 --> 00:52:54.890 align:middle line:90%
And I just feel great.

00:52:54.890 --> 00:53:00.036 align:middle line:84%
If I'm more relaxed, and if
I'm OK, then people around me

00:53:00.036 --> 00:53:03.340 align:middle line:84%
are probably going to
be more relaxed and OK.

00:53:03.340 --> 00:53:05.890 align:middle line:84%
Instead of just immediately
getting upset when something

00:53:05.890 --> 00:53:08.400 align:middle line:84%
irritates you, you
might think, OK, well,

00:53:08.400 --> 00:53:10.750 align:middle line:84%
maybe this person does have
something going on, whereas,

00:53:10.750 --> 00:53:12.715 align:middle line:84%
before, you wouldn't--
you would just get mad

00:53:12.715 --> 00:53:15.740 align:middle line:84%
and call that individual
a name or, you know,

00:53:15.740 --> 00:53:17.310 align:middle line:90%
just swear or something.

00:53:17.310 --> 00:53:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And some of those
habits are bad.

00:53:19.680 --> 00:53:22.070 align:middle line:84%
Losing your temper in traffic,
getting yourself riled up.

00:53:22.070 --> 00:53:26.440 align:middle line:84%
He run on my bumper, horsed
around in front of me,

00:53:26.440 --> 00:53:29.250 align:middle line:84%
and turned right in front of
me again, and turned right

00:53:29.250 --> 00:53:30.250 align:middle line:90%
there, right in front of me.

00:53:30.250 --> 00:53:33.190 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you know, he could
have waited two seconds.

00:53:33.190 --> 00:53:34.880 align:middle line:84%
If I hadn't have
been, you know, going

00:53:34.880 --> 00:53:37.630 align:middle line:84%
through this
mindfulness class, I'm

00:53:37.630 --> 00:53:39.630 align:middle line:84%
not going to tell you what I
would have done because I don't

00:53:39.630 --> 00:53:40.960 align:middle line:90%
want to incriminate myself.

00:53:40.960 --> 00:53:45.180 align:middle line:84%
So it's really just
becoming in touch with myself

00:53:45.180 --> 00:53:46.890 align:middle line:90%
and realizing who I am.

00:53:46.890 --> 00:53:50.810 align:middle line:84%
And as a result
of that, be calmer,

00:53:50.810 --> 00:53:53.680 align:middle line:84%
feel better, have
less pain, have

00:53:53.680 --> 00:53:56.670 align:middle line:90%
less anxiety, less depression.

00:53:56.670 --> 00:54:01.710 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness it just makes me
think of how everything is,

00:54:01.710 --> 00:54:03.100 align:middle line:90%
how everything actually is.

00:54:03.100 --> 00:54:07.942 align:middle line:84%
For example, we do-- we had
to do a eating exercise.

00:54:07.942 --> 00:54:09.660 align:middle line:84%
And being in the
military, we usually

00:54:09.660 --> 00:54:13.125 align:middle line:84%
eat-- you know, eat
quick because we always

00:54:13.125 --> 00:54:14.120 align:middle line:90%
have something else to do.

00:54:14.120 --> 00:54:17.990 align:middle line:84%
I wolf my food down
because of habit.

00:54:17.990 --> 00:54:19.630 align:middle line:90%
Military, you know.

00:54:19.630 --> 00:54:22.730 align:middle line:84%
I had never really
taken time to what

00:54:22.730 --> 00:54:27.140 align:middle line:84%
I call savor the food that
I really-- that I eat,

00:54:27.140 --> 00:54:28.000 align:middle line:90%
that I consume.

00:54:28.000 --> 00:54:32.280 align:middle line:84%
And that's still, right
now, a struggle for me,

00:54:32.280 --> 00:54:35.140 align:middle line:90%
to sit and enjoy a meal.

00:54:35.140 --> 00:54:37.490 align:middle line:84%
Doing this mindful
exercise I got to be

00:54:37.490 --> 00:54:39.760 align:middle line:90%
able to actually taste it.

00:54:39.760 --> 00:54:44.356 align:middle line:84%
I found out that all my
taste buds do work, you know.

00:54:44.356 --> 00:54:47.590 align:middle line:84%
And food is delicious
if you take to eat it.

00:54:47.590 --> 00:54:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And slow down and
actually taste what you eat

00:54:53.160 --> 00:54:54.780 align:middle line:90%
is a challenge to me.

00:54:54.780 --> 00:55:00.120 align:middle line:84%
But now I take time to connect
with myself and my thoughts

00:55:00.120 --> 00:55:02.656 align:middle line:90%
and just to be OK with me.

00:55:02.656 --> 00:55:04.880 align:middle line:84%
So that's what
mindfulness is to me.

00:55:04.880 --> 00:55:06.340 align:middle line:90%
For me, it's slow motion.

00:55:06.340 --> 00:55:09.960 align:middle line:84%
It is my choice to slow
things down, to take a breath,

00:55:09.960 --> 00:55:12.010 align:middle line:84%
to snap it all back
into perspective.

00:55:12.010 --> 00:55:16.970 align:middle line:84%
It makes me-- or, well,
or it invites me to slow

00:55:16.970 --> 00:55:21.540 align:middle line:90%
down, Concentrate on self.

00:55:21.540 --> 00:55:23.680 align:middle line:84%
I've learned
structural activity,

00:55:23.680 --> 00:55:26.740 align:middle line:90%
which was important to have.

00:55:26.740 --> 00:55:31.240 align:middle line:84%
I never considered
walking meditation.

00:55:31.240 --> 00:55:34.653 align:middle line:84%
For example, I was walking--
when outside of this building,

00:55:34.653 --> 00:55:40.105 align:middle line:84%
and I just was
free, feeling like I

00:55:40.105 --> 00:55:41.170 align:middle line:90%
was, you know, just free.

00:55:41.170 --> 00:55:42.770 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have any problems.

00:55:42.770 --> 00:55:45.570 align:middle line:84%
And the thing that makes this
different from regular walking

00:55:45.570 --> 00:55:49.030 align:middle line:84%
is that your focus
is desperately

00:55:49.030 --> 00:55:53.250 align:middle line:84%
on the slowest motion of
steps that you can take.

00:55:53.250 --> 00:55:54.020 align:middle line:90%
You just walk.

00:55:54.020 --> 00:55:56.610 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, you pay
attention to where you're going,

00:55:56.610 --> 00:55:59.230 align:middle line:90%
but you tune everything out.

00:55:59.230 --> 00:56:01.520 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like slow
motion, which, to me, is most

00:56:01.520 --> 00:56:03.580 align:middle line:84%
of what mindfulness
represents, putting

00:56:03.580 --> 00:56:04.967 align:middle line:90%
everything in slow motion.

00:56:04.967 --> 00:56:09.310 align:middle line:84%
And you can really,
really relax.

00:56:09.310 --> 00:56:12.040 align:middle line:84%
It does take
every bit of focus,

00:56:12.040 --> 00:56:13.637 align:middle line:84%
so you're not thinking
about the past,

00:56:13.637 --> 00:56:14.870 align:middle line:84%
you're not thinking
about the future.

00:56:14.870 --> 00:56:17.730 align:middle line:84%
You're just thinking, wow, this
is a neat experience, to walk.

00:56:17.730 --> 00:56:30.330 align:middle line:90%


00:56:30.330 --> 00:56:32.460 align:middle line:84%
It's not easy being
a teenager these days.

00:56:32.460 --> 00:56:35.070 align:middle line:84%
The constant pressure of
fitting in, growing up, going

00:56:35.070 --> 00:56:37.620 align:middle line:84%
through puberty, and keeping
up with the world that moves

00:56:37.620 --> 00:56:41.380 align:middle line:84%
faster than ever before
can adversely affect

00:56:41.380 --> 00:56:42.870 align:middle line:90%
the mind of the adolescent.

00:56:42.870 --> 00:56:44.630 align:middle line:84%
The Mindfulness
in Schools Project

00:56:44.630 --> 00:56:47.570 align:middle line:84%
was created when some
teaching colleagues

00:56:47.570 --> 00:56:51.150 align:middle line:84%
and I shared an
ambition to bring

00:56:51.150 --> 00:56:54.860 align:middle line:84%
together two things that were
really close to our hearts.

00:56:54.860 --> 00:56:57.150 align:middle line:84%
One was mindfulness
practice, which we've

00:56:57.150 --> 00:56:59.580 align:middle line:84%
been doing for many
years, and the other was

00:56:59.580 --> 00:57:01.640 align:middle line:90%
the art of classroom teaching.

00:57:01.640 --> 00:57:04.320 align:middle line:10%
And we ended up
writing a nine week

00:57:04.320 --> 00:57:06.350 align:middle line:10%
classroom introduction
to mindfulness,

00:57:06.350 --> 00:57:08.060 align:middle line:10%
which we called Dot B.

00:57:08.060 --> 00:57:11.570 align:middle line:84%
And Dot B was really our
answer to the challenge

00:57:11.570 --> 00:57:15.640 align:middle line:84%
we set ourselves, which was
to write a mindfulness course

00:57:15.640 --> 00:57:19.410 align:middle line:84%
which was engaging,
fun, memorable,

00:57:19.410 --> 00:57:22.680 align:middle line:84%
and also of practical
use on the roller coaster

00:57:22.680 --> 00:57:24.850 align:middle line:90%
that is adolescence.

00:57:24.850 --> 00:57:28.280 align:middle line:84%
We will spend a lot of time
cramming kids' brains with all

00:57:28.280 --> 00:57:30.560 align:middle line:84%
the facts that they
need for their history,

00:57:30.560 --> 00:57:34.690 align:middle line:84%
or their geography, or their
languages, or their sciences,

00:57:34.690 --> 00:57:39.110 align:middle line:84%
but we never really turn the
lens inwards on their minds.

00:57:39.110 --> 00:57:40.740 align:middle line:84%
And the great thing
about mindfulness

00:57:40.740 --> 00:57:45.680 align:middle line:84%
is that it gives you a tool to
deploy when you find yourself

00:57:45.680 --> 00:57:47.550 align:middle line:90%
in a stressful situation.

00:57:47.550 --> 00:57:52.160 align:middle line:84%
And you know, OK,
if I just pause,

00:57:52.160 --> 00:57:54.640 align:middle line:84%
if I notice how my breathing
is, I don't necessarily

00:57:54.640 --> 00:57:58.980 align:middle line:84%
try to control it, I just notice
where it is, it switches me out

00:57:58.980 --> 00:58:02.980 align:middle line:84%
of the thinking mode, the
ruminative, cognitive, mode,

00:58:02.980 --> 00:58:05.120 align:middle line:90%
and into the sensing mode.

00:58:05.120 --> 00:58:08.940 align:middle line:84%
And what a lot of research
is telling us at the moment,

00:58:08.940 --> 00:58:11.510 align:middle line:84%
and what I know from my own
experience and from the kids

00:58:11.510 --> 00:58:14.491 align:middle line:84%
that I taught, is that our kids
are pretty tough on themselves

00:58:14.491 --> 00:58:15.190 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:58:15.190 --> 00:58:18.640 align:middle line:84%
I think it's the stress,
and anxiety, and all

00:58:18.640 --> 00:58:19.860 align:middle line:84%
of these things,
and achievement,

00:58:19.860 --> 00:58:22.580 align:middle line:84%
the achievement ethic that
we have in the culture.

00:58:22.580 --> 00:58:25.171 align:middle line:84%
All of these things actually
put tremendous pressure on kids

00:58:25.171 --> 00:58:25.870 align:middle line:90%
now.

00:58:25.870 --> 00:58:29.800 align:middle line:84%
In fact, in today's world,
teens are more under pressure

00:58:29.800 --> 00:58:33.220 align:middle line:84%
and experiencing higher levels
of stress than ever before.

00:58:33.220 --> 00:58:35.490 align:middle line:84%
And increasing
demand in technology,

00:58:35.490 --> 00:58:39.260 align:middle line:84%
academic preparation, and
life transitions all result

00:58:39.260 --> 00:58:41.130 align:middle line:84%
in physical and
emotional stressors,

00:58:41.130 --> 00:58:45.820 align:middle line:84%
such as bad temper,
anxiety, depression,

00:58:45.820 --> 00:58:47.440 align:middle line:90%
and attention-deficit disorder.

00:58:47.440 --> 00:58:49.400 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to
find out more, so I

00:58:49.400 --> 00:58:52.720 align:middle line:84%
went to the University
of California San Diego,

00:58:52.720 --> 00:58:54.870 align:middle line:84%
the center of
mindfulness, and spoke

00:58:54.870 --> 00:58:57.110 align:middle line:84%
with director Steve
Hickman, and course

00:58:57.110 --> 00:58:58.870 align:middle line:90%
instructor, Lorraine Hobbs.

00:58:58.870 --> 00:59:00.885 align:middle line:84%
We were running
groups, mindfulness

00:59:00.885 --> 00:59:03.950 align:middle line:84%
based stress reduction groups,
for adults for several years.

00:59:03.950 --> 00:59:07.360 align:middle line:84%
And then as we talked to people,
other people who had taken

00:59:07.360 --> 00:59:09.560 align:middle line:84%
the mindfulness based
stress reduction course

00:59:09.560 --> 00:59:11.310 align:middle line:84%
and had seen what it
had done for them,

00:59:11.310 --> 00:59:12.920 align:middle line:84%
they were sort of
thinking, wow, you know,

00:59:12.920 --> 00:59:15.440 align:middle line:84%
my teenager could really benefit
from this, all the stress

00:59:15.440 --> 00:59:17.290 align:middle line:90%
of teen life these days.

00:59:17.290 --> 00:59:20.100 align:middle line:84%
Almost my entire life,
and as far as I remember,

00:59:20.100 --> 00:59:23.130 align:middle line:84%
I've been dealing with
depression, anger,

00:59:23.130 --> 00:59:24.740 align:middle line:90%
and a good deal of anxiety.

00:59:24.740 --> 00:59:28.260 align:middle line:84%
Not being able to handle
my emotions well enough.

00:59:28.260 --> 00:59:31.250 align:middle line:90%
I had a short fuse.

00:59:31.250 --> 00:59:34.080 align:middle line:90%
Um, and I have ADHD.

00:59:34.080 --> 00:59:37.760 align:middle line:84%
I was struggling
with my depression.

00:59:37.760 --> 00:59:41.310 align:middle line:84%
I would fight with my
parents a lot and, like,

00:59:41.310 --> 00:59:42.520 align:middle line:90%
I would take it out on them.

00:59:42.520 --> 00:59:44.560 align:middle line:84%
It got to the point where
I started lashing out

00:59:44.560 --> 00:59:47.210 align:middle line:84%
at my parents, so
my mom came to me,

00:59:47.210 --> 00:59:49.010 align:middle line:84%
like, OK, we need
to find something

00:59:49.010 --> 00:59:53.400 align:middle line:84%
to control your temper and to
control your ADHD way more.

00:59:53.400 --> 00:59:58.710 align:middle line:84%
And she found this mindfulness
thing and I was like, fine,

00:59:58.710 --> 00:59:59.550 align:middle line:90%
I'll try it.

00:59:59.550 --> 01:00:02.120 align:middle line:84%
I'd seen the website for
the mindfulness center

01:00:02.120 --> 01:00:04.370 align:middle line:84%
and kind of saw that
there was a teen group.

01:00:04.370 --> 01:00:06.530 align:middle line:84%
So I came home one day and
told my husband about it

01:00:06.530 --> 01:00:08.690 align:middle line:84%
and I said I'm just going
to tell her she's going.

01:00:08.690 --> 01:00:12.600 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't really sure,
like-- was it meditation?

01:00:12.600 --> 01:00:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Was it like a group,
therapy group?

01:00:14.790 --> 01:00:16.200 align:middle line:90%
I wasn't sure.

01:00:16.200 --> 01:00:19.220 align:middle line:84%
And then I came and I kind
of got a gist of what it was.

01:00:19.220 --> 01:00:23.830 align:middle line:84%
I hadn't got the practice down,
but was less resistant to go.

01:00:23.830 --> 01:00:27.440 align:middle line:84%
So after maybe two
months, I liked it a lot.

01:00:27.440 --> 01:00:29.820 align:middle line:90%
I've tried other stuff.

01:00:29.820 --> 01:00:32.785 align:middle line:84%
I've tried to the
count to 10 strategy.

01:00:32.785 --> 01:00:34.480 align:middle line:90%
That doesn't really work.

01:00:34.480 --> 01:00:36.260 align:middle line:84%
After the first
day, I kind of just

01:00:36.260 --> 01:00:38.000 align:middle line:84%
realized there's
no turning back.

01:00:38.000 --> 01:00:40.750 align:middle line:84%
I can't go back because
where am I going to go.

01:00:40.750 --> 01:00:44.030 align:middle line:84%
There is no-- so I was
like I better do it right.

01:00:44.030 --> 01:00:46.620 align:middle line:84%
After the first couple
times, I really look forward

01:00:46.620 --> 01:00:47.980 align:middle line:90%
to coming here and doing it.

01:00:47.980 --> 01:00:51.520 align:middle line:84%
First few times, I was
like this makes sense to me.

01:00:51.520 --> 01:00:54.250 align:middle line:84%
I can actually-- I
can actually do it.

01:00:54.250 --> 01:00:56.890 align:middle line:84%
This is the first thing I've
ever done that was really

01:00:56.890 --> 01:00:59.290 align:middle line:84%
all about the mind,
which, I think,

01:00:59.290 --> 01:01:01.660 align:middle line:84%
helps get to the
root of the problems.

01:01:01.660 --> 01:01:04.200 align:middle line:84%
They started teaching little
intricate things they have,

01:01:04.200 --> 01:01:07.660 align:middle line:84%
the finger tracings, 7/11, self
check-in, all these different

01:01:07.660 --> 01:01:09.070 align:middle line:90%
have been perfected.

01:01:09.070 --> 01:01:14.930 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness, um, teaches for
you to be mindful of yourself,

01:01:14.930 --> 01:01:17.390 align:middle line:90%
to be one with yourself.

01:01:17.390 --> 01:01:19.890 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness is
being not mindless.

01:01:19.890 --> 01:01:22.690 align:middle line:84%
You take a moment and
you just take a breath.

01:01:22.690 --> 01:01:26.105 align:middle line:84%
And that calms me down
a lot, especially when

01:01:26.105 --> 01:01:29.840 align:middle line:90%
you're really anxious or mad.

01:01:29.840 --> 01:01:30.850 align:middle line:90%
That one helps me.

01:01:30.850 --> 01:01:33.330 align:middle line:84%
It's like if you have
an uncomfortable feeling

01:01:33.330 --> 01:01:36.980 align:middle line:84%
of sadness or anger, you're not
using those tools to exactly

01:01:36.980 --> 01:01:40.590 align:middle line:84%
run away from it, but to
instead examine it in a way

01:01:40.590 --> 01:01:44.070 align:middle line:84%
that you're able to let it
go, but at the same time

01:01:44.070 --> 01:01:48.120 align:middle line:84%
dissect it and, like, understand
the feeling it in a more, like,

01:01:48.120 --> 01:01:51.270 align:middle line:84%
objective way, without getting
attached to it as well.

01:01:51.270 --> 01:01:53.597 align:middle line:90%
Bring yourself in and really--

01:01:53.597 --> 01:01:56.579 align:middle line:90%
[SIGH]

01:01:56.579 --> 01:01:57.600 align:middle line:90%
You know?

01:01:57.600 --> 01:02:01.380 align:middle line:84%
Mindfulness has really helped
me not to control my thoughts

01:02:01.380 --> 01:02:04.370 align:middle line:84%
because you're never really
going to be able to control

01:02:04.370 --> 01:02:05.400 align:middle line:90%
your thoughts 100%.

01:02:05.400 --> 01:02:06.960 align:middle line:84%
Your mind will always
wonder to things.

01:02:06.960 --> 01:02:10.030 align:middle line:84%
But it's about, like,
redirecting your thoughts

01:02:10.030 --> 01:02:13.720 align:middle line:84%
and reining in your thoughts
and being able to bring them

01:02:13.720 --> 01:02:15.320 align:middle line:90%
to something more positive.

01:02:15.320 --> 01:02:18.510 align:middle line:84%
I think it's, like, for me,
like, it's not about forgetting

01:02:18.510 --> 01:02:20.220 align:middle line:84%
your emotions or,
like, what's happening,

01:02:20.220 --> 01:02:23.060 align:middle line:84%
it's more just, like,
detaching yourself

01:02:23.060 --> 01:02:28.910 align:middle line:84%
from the-- like, your
emotion, but at the same time,

01:02:28.910 --> 01:02:30.590 align:middle line:90%
observing it and accepting it.

01:02:30.590 --> 01:02:32.678 align:middle line:84%
If my problem was
this cushion, like,

01:02:32.678 --> 01:02:36.040 align:middle line:90%
I'd-- sit on your problem.

01:02:36.040 --> 01:02:38.391 align:middle line:90%
Learn to be with your problem.

01:02:38.391 --> 01:02:41.600 align:middle line:84%
The life of a teenager
now is probably

01:02:41.600 --> 01:02:44.957 align:middle line:84%
far more stressful even
then when I went through it.

01:02:44.957 --> 01:02:49.590 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, why not
give your teen the tools

01:02:49.590 --> 01:02:53.180 align:middle line:84%
to learn how to manage their
own stress, like we're all,

01:02:53.180 --> 01:02:54.870 align:middle line:84%
you know, as adults,
trying to learn them?

01:02:54.870 --> 01:02:58.590 align:middle line:84%
I have the tools now to
understand what I'm feeling.

01:02:58.590 --> 01:03:01.820 align:middle line:84%
And because I'm really shy feel,
so like, when I go and, like,

01:03:01.820 --> 01:03:03.240 align:middle line:84%
try to performance
in front of people,

01:03:03.240 --> 01:03:05.290 align:middle line:90%
I get really, really nervous.

01:03:05.290 --> 01:03:10.030 align:middle line:84%
So I have used mindfulness for
that because it calms me down

01:03:10.030 --> 01:03:12.100 align:middle line:84%
and I feel more
comfortable then.

01:03:12.100 --> 01:03:15.100 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

01:03:15.100 --> 01:03:17.996 align:middle line:90%


01:03:17.996 --> 01:03:20.750 align:middle line:84%
I try and hide
all of my anxiety

01:03:20.750 --> 01:03:22.960 align:middle line:84%
and depression and
stuff, but with my mom,

01:03:22.960 --> 01:03:23.950 align:middle line:90%
she sees everything.

01:03:23.950 --> 01:03:26.090 align:middle line:84%
And so she's-- she
says she's really

01:03:26.090 --> 01:03:31.870 align:middle line:84%
noticed a huge difference in
my attention and my moods.

01:03:31.870 --> 01:03:36.500 align:middle line:84%
So I guess that's proof of
the effectiveness of it.

01:03:36.500 --> 01:03:38.840 align:middle line:84%
I learned not to, like,
judge myself as much

01:03:38.840 --> 01:03:41.600 align:middle line:90%
and think about the present.

01:03:41.600 --> 01:03:46.010 align:middle line:84%
Because when I think about
the past or the future, like,

01:03:46.010 --> 01:03:50.890 align:middle line:84%
that's what causes
me a lot of anxiety.

01:03:50.890 --> 01:03:52.910 align:middle line:84%
I've got like a
mile long fuse now.

01:03:52.910 --> 01:03:55.260 align:middle line:90%
It's-- it's ridiculous.

01:03:55.260 --> 01:03:56.560 align:middle line:90%
It's really healthy.

01:03:56.560 --> 01:03:58.760 align:middle line:84%
If you're making eggs,
you're mindfully making eggs.

01:03:58.760 --> 01:04:01.980 align:middle line:84%
It's an experience
now, not just a task.

01:04:01.980 --> 01:04:04.540 align:middle line:84%
I used to wake up like three,
four times in the night.

01:04:04.540 --> 01:04:06.960 align:middle line:84%
And now, I only wake
up, like, twice.

01:04:06.960 --> 01:04:10.550 align:middle line:84%
But it actually really helped
me and my stress levels.

01:04:10.550 --> 01:04:13.470 align:middle line:84%
I've noticed a huge
amount of change.

01:04:13.470 --> 01:04:16.858 align:middle line:84%
My mood swings aren't
nearly as violent.

01:04:16.858 --> 01:04:18.670 align:middle line:90%
My stress is completely down.

01:04:18.670 --> 01:04:20.820 align:middle line:84%
I think I'm more
confident, more alive.

01:04:20.820 --> 01:04:23.070 align:middle line:84%
I was in a very
sorry state before I

01:04:23.070 --> 01:04:26.990 align:middle line:84%
discovered the practice, before
I discovered mindfulness.

01:04:26.990 --> 01:04:29.500 align:middle line:90%
You see, I'm bipolar, type two.

01:04:29.500 --> 01:04:33.810 align:middle line:84%
And as the diagnose--
well, tells you,

01:04:33.810 --> 01:04:38.440 align:middle line:84%
I feel extremely deep
and powerful emotions

01:04:38.440 --> 01:04:43.310 align:middle line:84%
at almost any time,
switching very rapidly.

01:04:43.310 --> 01:04:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And for awhile, I felt as if I
was a victim of these feelings,

01:04:49.890 --> 01:04:51.590 align:middle line:84%
like they were something
that I couldn't control,

01:04:51.590 --> 01:04:54.690 align:middle line:84%
like they were a
monster inside me.

01:04:54.690 --> 01:04:58.500 align:middle line:84%
But then, a year ago, I started
going to the mindfulness group.

01:04:58.500 --> 01:05:03.580 align:middle line:84%
And the changes that have
happened since then, I

01:05:03.580 --> 01:05:06.170 align:middle line:84%
can't believe how
different things are

01:05:06.170 --> 01:05:07.940 align:middle line:90%
now, much better my life is.

01:05:07.940 --> 01:05:11.110 align:middle line:84%
I think the ambition of the
Mindfulness in Schools Project

01:05:11.110 --> 01:05:12.970 align:middle line:84%
is partly just to
raise awareness

01:05:12.970 --> 01:05:16.775 align:middle line:84%
of what mindfulness is and
give all kids a taste of it.

01:05:16.775 --> 01:05:18.905 align:middle line:84%
You know, we're not
trying to convert everyone

01:05:18.905 --> 01:05:21.350 align:middle line:84%
into deep mindfulness
practitioners.

01:05:21.350 --> 01:05:23.055 align:middle line:84%
We're just trying to make
them aware of what it

01:05:23.055 --> 01:05:24.870 align:middle line:90%
is because it's common sense.

01:05:24.870 --> 01:05:28.340 align:middle line:10%
This, to me, seems to be
the most fundamental thing

01:05:28.340 --> 01:05:30.090 align:middle line:10%
that we should teach our kids.

01:05:30.090 --> 01:05:32.560 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing else to
be taught if you haven't

01:05:32.560 --> 01:05:34.450 align:middle line:90%
learned how to pay attention.

01:05:34.450 --> 01:05:37.130 align:middle line:84%
So when you teach mindfulness
at home to your kids,

01:05:37.130 --> 01:05:39.710 align:middle line:84%
you're actually giving them
this incredible source of

01:05:39.710 --> 01:05:41.400 align:middle line:90%
social and emotional learning.

01:05:41.400 --> 01:05:43.390 align:middle line:84%
You're giving them a
source of resilience.

01:05:43.390 --> 01:05:46.640 align:middle line:84%
So those kids actually
have a different feel

01:05:46.640 --> 01:05:50.000 align:middle line:84%
than kids who have a mind, of
course, but don't see the mind.

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:51.530 align:middle line:84%
You've got to
train the teachers.

01:05:51.530 --> 01:05:53.240 align:middle line:84%
If the teachers
aren't being mindful,

01:05:53.240 --> 01:05:55.170 align:middle line:84%
how are the kids ever
going to be mindful.

01:05:55.170 --> 01:05:57.860 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
we should be thinking

01:05:57.860 --> 01:06:00.231 align:middle line:84%
that every kid in
the school is going

01:06:00.231 --> 01:06:02.130 align:middle line:84%
to want to get up in the
morning and practice mindfulness

01:06:02.130 --> 01:06:03.510 align:middle line:90%
for half an hour.

01:06:03.510 --> 01:06:06.350 align:middle line:84%
I think it is realistic
for every kid in school

01:06:06.350 --> 01:06:09.430 align:middle line:84%
to be aware of mindfulness,
to know what it is,

01:06:09.430 --> 01:06:11.530 align:middle line:84%
to have enjoyed
learning about it,

01:06:11.530 --> 01:06:14.580 align:middle line:84%
to have valued the experience,
so that's some of them,

01:06:14.580 --> 01:06:17.510 align:middle line:84%
yes, do go on to become
mindfulness teachers.

01:06:17.510 --> 01:06:20.760 align:middle line:90%


01:06:20.760 --> 01:06:24.180 align:middle line:10%
In a sense, we human
beings on our own.

01:06:24.180 --> 01:06:28.280 align:middle line:10%
It may be time for us to
grow up and-- or grow down

01:06:28.280 --> 01:06:32.550 align:middle line:10%
and become planetary adults.

01:06:32.550 --> 01:06:35.330 align:middle line:84%
And that would
mean, in some sense,

01:06:35.330 --> 01:06:40.060 align:middle line:84%
a deep experiential grounding
in interconnectedness.

01:06:40.060 --> 01:06:43.990 align:middle line:84%
And if that's so, then
maybe we have a certain kind

01:06:43.990 --> 01:06:45.720 align:middle line:84%
of responsibility
if we are ever going

01:06:45.720 --> 01:06:48.180 align:middle line:84%
to grow into being
a planetary adult

01:06:48.180 --> 01:06:52.890 align:middle line:84%
to actually inhabit the present
moment or rediscover it.

